title: christmas cookie balls
directions: Mix flour, butter, nuts and salt; form balls. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add shortening and applesauce.
Mix together for 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 more minutes.
Stir in raisins and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Top with English or black walnuts and maraschino cherries.
(Maraschino cherries may be added to batter.)

title: no-peek chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine uncooked rice, cream soup and onion soup mix, blended with water. Arrange chicken on soup mixture. Cover. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and rice is done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add sour cream and stir until smooth.
Cook until bubbly.
Fold in green beans.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread Velveeta cheese on top.
Top with cornflakes mixed with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet potatoes souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour into mixing bowl.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Add rolled oats and mix well.
Spread half of crumb mixture in greased 8-inch square pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: gavin's favorite chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Roll chicken in crescent rolls.
In a bowl, mix the cheese, milk and cream of chicken soup.
Pour half of this mixture into a baking dish.
Put crescent rolls in dish and cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: taco salad appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese and dressing mix in a bowl; mix well. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer with lettuce, bell pepper, tomatoes and olives.
Pour salsa over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with fat-free sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put beef, onion and celery in pan and brown.
Combine remaining ingredients, then add to meat.
Cook on low heat for approximately 1 hour.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, sour cream, butter, eggs and sugar. Stir in muffin mix and pour into well-greased casserole. Bake at 350° until knife inserted into middle comes out clean, about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Lower to 325° for glass dishes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Place beef roast, water and bay leaves in a large kettle or Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 3 hours. Remove meat from broth; cool. Add onions, carrots and celery to broth. Cook for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Cut meat into bite-size pieces; add to broth. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley, seasonings, beans, peas and kidney beans. Cook until vegetables are done, about 10 minutes. Add macaroni and heat through. Remove bay leaves. Ladle into soup bowls; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Yield: about 40 servings (10 quarts).

title: orange cranberry relish
directions: Place hot water in blender and run blender until dissolved. Add orange, celery and sugar and turn blender on for one minute. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add water or orange juice, cranberries and walnuts.
Turn on blender for 4 seconds.
Pour into quart mold and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix fat and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on baking pan.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown. Yields 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form ball.
Can be rolled in chopped nuts.

title: fried vegetable plate
directions: Add beaten egg to vegetables.
Mix in flour to coat vegetables.
Place vegetables and flour in strainer and shake out extra flour.
Flour should only coat vegetables.
Fry on medium heat until the vegetables are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add rice, mushroom soup, celery, onion soup mix, chicken soup and water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: shrimp eggroll
directions: Preparing The Ingredients:
Peel all the shells off of the shrimp and wash them with salt to dissolve its slime.
Wash with cold water after and set them to dry.

title: caramelitas
directions: Combine 1 C. flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and salt. Stir in butter; mix well.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: reception punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until dissolved; cool.
Combine juices, ginger ale, sparkling water and fruits.
Pour into punch bowl and add crushed ice.
Drop in sherbet by spoonfuls.
Makes 20 to 30 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until mixture is mealy and set aside.
Mix egg yolks and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine flour, sugar and salt, then gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until thickened.
Pour half of the hot filling slowly over the beaten egg yolks.
Return all to pan and cook for 2 or 3 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly. Cool and add butter and vanilla.
Sprinkle half of peanut butter mixture on crust evenly.
Pour custard on top and sprinkle remaining half of peanut butter mixture on the custard.
Top with meringue.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place pecans in the pan; then add the roll dough.
Sprinkle pudding mix and cinnamon over the rolls.
Mix melted butter and brown sugar; pour over rolls.
Cover and allow to rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, then invert onto a plate. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: cucumber cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Peel and grate cucumber; drain.
Add to cream cheese and blend well.
Add mayonnaise, sweet and sour dressing and salt.
Add green food coloring for desired shade.
Spread on bread slices and cut.
Yields 8 to 10 dozen (party size).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; top with salt, pepper, butter and crackers.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan to cool.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, using only 1/2 package of bread crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato chow chow(for canning)
directions: Pack into hot, sterile jars and seal.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir soda into pulp. Add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla; sift flour and add.
Mix. Bake in well-greased baking pan at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheese-corn pudding
directions: Saute onion in butter. Blend in flour. Gradually add milk and cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add pimiento, sugar and marjoram.
Stir in corn and eggs.
Pour into shallow buttered casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and dot with additional butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, bananas and eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.
Will make 2 loaves.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk. Mix well. Sift together flour, allspice, cinnamon, salt, soda and cocoa, mixing with creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with 1/2 to 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: rinktum ditty
directions: Saute' onion in butter until tender.
Puree tomatoes in blender, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar to the onions and butter and heat.
When this begins to bubble, slowly add cheese, stirring constantly until all the cheese is blended into the mixture.
Slowly add the egg, stirring constantly and cook an additional minute.

title: crescents
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon; shape with spoon and hand, placing on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes in a 350° oven.	Roll in confectioners sugar when cool.

title: kielbasa-pasta supper
directions: In butter, stir-fry onion, green pepper, mushrooms, garlic powder and oregano.
Add kielbasa (bite-sized).
Heat through; stir in Parmesan cheese.
Serve over buttered pasta with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour
into
greased
and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for
45 to 50 minutes.
Frost with Coca-Cola Icing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple-oatmeal bars
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Spread half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange the apples over the crumbs.
Dot with the butter and sprinkle with the white sugar.
Cover the apples with the remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Slice butter in thin slices in bowl.
Add brown sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; beat.
Add flavoring and beat.
Stir in by hand the nuts and chocolate chips.
Grease large pan or 2 square cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Remove to wire rack or a storage container.

title: corn pone
directions: Bring water to boil with salt, sugar, pepper and onion. Combine cornmeal and 1/3 of water.
Slowly add remainder of water; beat vigorously.
Cool.
Form patties 1/2-inch thick.
Fry in 350° in deep oil until brown about 1 minute on each side.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add sugar.
Let set overnight. Drain pineapple the next morning if there is any liquid.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Add chicken broth and boil on high 10-15 minutes. Bring to low heat. Pour in soups, milk and sour cream. Mix. Add onions. Add bacon. Simmer on low for one hour. Sprinkle cheese on top before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Let cool.
Add thawed strawberries, pecans, bananas and pineapple.
Pour into glass dish 1/2 of mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Spread sour cream on top and cover with remainder of Jell-O mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Blend in vanilla and rum extract.
Sift flour with salt.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Reserve 2 tablespoons sour cream. Blend soda with reserved sour cream.
Add to batter.

title: french toast
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip each piece of bread in batter until coated.
Fry in skillet in 1 tablespoon hot shortening on both sides until golden brown.
Serve with syrup or honey.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Combine bread stuffing with mushrooms and juice, butter and cheese.
Spread over flank steak.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Fasten with skewers or string.
Pour oil in slow cooker.
Roll steak in oil, coating all sides.
Prepare gravy.
Pour gravy, wine and onions over meat.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours. Remove meat from pot and slice.
Add jelly to sauce and stir until dissolved.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed. Cover; chill. Makes 3 cups.

title: honey baked apples
directions: Core apples to within 1/2-inch of bottom.
In a cup, mix walnuts and raisins.
Fill the cored apples with the mixture and place in a baking dish.
In a small saucepan, combine the water, honey and cinnamon.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Remove cinnamon and pour over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until apples are tender, about 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and fill foil lined cup cake papers and place in freezer.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Chill until firm.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat all together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 45 minute at 375°.

title: pesto-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain; toss with oil.
Mix pesto, olives, vinegar and tomatoes in large bowl.
Arrange 2 cups macaroni and 2 cups spinach on olive mixture; repeat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Toss and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings (about 1/4 cup each), 500 calories per serving.

title: garlic cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend; slowly add milk.
Stir until thickened; add cheese and garlic, then salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve with pasta, just toss together.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Cut boned chicken into medium size pieces.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream (approximately 1/2 cup) with chicken until well coated. Add other ingredients and season to taste.
Chill and serve cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Heat peanut butter, oleo, brown sugar and vanilla in microwave.
Don't boil.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Put in jelly roll pan.
Cover with wax paper and roll out with rolling pin.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix dry Jello with cottage cheese.
Add pineapple, oranges, nuts, and raisins.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill at least 1 hour. Makes a good dessert.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In top of double boiler melt chips with milk and butter.
In a large bowl combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours and cut into small squares.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Dice chili peppers and spread over refried beans.

title: breakfast-in-a-bag
directions: Layer bacon in bottom of sandwich bag.
Fold top of bag over 3 or 4 times.
Punch a hole through folds with a sharp stick.
Brace stick to hold bag over coals until bacon starts to cook, coating sides and bottom of bag with grease.
Remove bag, open and pour eggs directly onto bacon.
Close bag, place back on stick and lean back over coals until eggs are cooked.
When finished, tear off top half of bag and eat directly from bag.
Tastes better than it looks!

title: stuffed baked apples
directions: Core each apple, making a large cavity.
Arrange apples in baking pan.
Fill cavities with raisins.
Combine lemon juice and apple juice and pour over apples.
Drizzle small amount of margarine into each cavity.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: garbanzo bean stew
directions: Cut sausages into bite size chunks.
Cut pepper into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Add 2 teaspoons juice from jar of hot peppers or to taste.
Heat and serve.
Add water while heating for desired juice level.
Serves 4 or one very hungry husband.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Beat milk and pudding until thick and smooth.
Add Cool Whip and ice cream.
Put on a graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: turtle sundae dessert
directions: Mix cake according to package directions. Set aside half of the batter. Pour remaining batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and make patties.
Beat egg in bowl.
Dip patties in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes, then fry in oil.

title: sherried fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Serve on jellied fruit salad.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, cocoa and spices together.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to oil mixture.
Add jam and nuts.
Using 3 (9-inch) pans, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato jelly
directions: Strain juice of tomatoes to remove the seeds.
Mix 1 part tomato juice with 1 part sugar.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: sour cream chocolate frosting
directions: Mix butter and cooled chocolate thoroughly.
Blend in sugar. Stir in sour cream and vanilla; beat until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: lemon bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix first 4 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: dirt dessert(serves approximately 20)
directions: You will need gummy worms, flowerpot and artificial flowers for this recipe.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine syrup, butter or margarine and pineapple juice in saucepan. Place over medium heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Place potatoes in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with pineapple tidbits and pecans.
Add syrup mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Baste every 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruitcake roll
directions: Mix crackers (mashed fine), raisins, cherries and chopped pecans. Melt oleo and marshmallows and pour over dry ingredients. Mix with your hands and make into 3 long rolls. Wrap in foil and freeze. When ready to serve, you can slice them like cookies.

title: cornbread delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Test by putting toothpick in center; if it doesn't stick to toothpick, it is done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and cook until clear and turns thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool and add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: green and white casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear; do not brown.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk. Add confectioners sugar while mixing. Continue adding sugar until the icing is thick enough to spread.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Prepare macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain. Combine all ingredients, except fried onions.
Pour half of mixture into 2-quart casserole, then add half of onion rings on top.
Pour remaining mixture over onions and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Let the jello and liquid set in refrigerator until it is like egg whites.
Then whip until like whipped cream.
Beat in cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in pineapple or cherries.
Add marshmallows.
Put in greased jello mold and set.

title: split pea soup
directions: Peas must be soaked overnight.
In a soup pot, put in peas and 6 cups of water.
Add bay leaves and salt and pepper to taste. Add in ham hock.
Simmer for an hour and a half.
Scoop out ham hock (discard).
Put peas (a few cups at a time) in a blender to puree.
Return soup to the pot and add carrots and potatoes (and hot dogs if you did not use a ham hock).
Add water, if soup is too thick.

title: red congealed salad
directions: Combine pineapple, Jell-O and sugar in saucepan and let boil 2 minutes; let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator to cool and serve.

title: 7 can casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Top with toasted sliced almonds.
Keep 7 cans and almonds on pantry shelf.
Great for emergency situations.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir Bisquick, milk, and cheese together until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto un-greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 - 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Mix together butter and garlic.
Brush over hot biscuits.

title: lemon sponge
directions: Beat whites separately and then mix all together.
Bake bottom and filling at the same time.
Makes 2 large and 1 small pie. Bake at about 400° until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick. Place sliced strawberries in a baked pie shell and pour cooled mixture over berries.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Brown meat and onions in shortening until browned and onions are soft.
Add water and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 50 minutes.

title: wild strawberry sun preserves(modern)
directions: Gather the leaves when plants are in bloom, leaving stems intact.
Tie stems in bundles and hang leaves in dry ventilated area.
Leaves must be thoroughly dry.
Then crumble (like green tea).
Store in sealed container in a dry, dark place.

title: white mountain pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together, except Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together thoroughly, then add cheese.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: 3 day cole slaw
directions: Combine vegetables; set aside.
Combine others and bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Pack in jars and cover.
Let stand for 3 days in refrigerator.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of casserole dish and add corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over corn and add 1/2 cup water.
Add onion and green pepper; season with salt and pepper.
Crumble ground beef over top; pour remaining tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water over top.
Cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies as directed; let cool.
Take half of brownies and crumble in the bottom of a large bowl.
Add half of the prepared pudding.
Add half of the Cool Whip and 3 Heath bars, then repeat.

title: sauerkraut pie
directions: Drain sauerkraut (most of the juice).
Put on bottom of pan. Slice sausage and cover all the sauerkraut with sausage.
Don't cook sausage.
Boil potatoes; drain most of the water out (leave a little water).
Mash potatoes and put chopped onions in potatoes. Mix well and put over your sausage.
Then put butter or oleo on and bake at 350°.
Cook until golden brown.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Melt butter in olive oil. Saute onion until translucent.
Add garlic; simmer 1 minute.
Add broccoli and wine or broth; simmer 3 minutes.
In a large bowl mix pasta with mixture.
Toss well.
Serve immediately with grated cheese for topping.

title: old fashioned chili
directions: Brown the meat, onions and pepper. Add the rest of the ingredients and cook on low heat for about one hour.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Store in a sealed container. To make 1 cup:
Put
tablespoons
and 1 teaspoon mix into a cup; add hot water.

title: pineapple-nut cake
directions: Throw all together in a large bowl and mix with a spoon by hand (not by mixer).
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan (I use a glass pan).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cake will be moist.

title: crystal marmalade
directions: Wash fruit well.
Cut in small slices.
Mix 1 cup of fruit to 3 cups of water.
Let stand for 2 plus hours in a glass container; then boil (hard) for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook green beans according to directions.
Boil potatoes and mash.
Mix hamburger, soup and green beans.
Place in a casserole dish.
Place mashed potatoes on top.
Add cheese, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until mashed potatoes are crisp on top.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar together.
Set aside 5 minutes. Mix flour and salt together.
Add to yeast mixture.
In a separate bowl, beat egg and set aside.
Shape pretzels.
Brush with egg. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: top of stove baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble; set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in bacon drippings.
Pour off grease.
Add beans, sugar, vinegar, catsup and bacon.
Simmer until liquid is thickened to desired consistency, about 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake factory pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients together just until coated and crumbly. Press onto the bottom and 2/3 cup the sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan. Bake for 5 minutes at 350°. Set aside.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: You will need 24 small (1-inch) foil baking cups.

title: so easy chicken dish
directions: Place chicken in 8 inch x 8 inch oven proof dish. Put one slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and wine in small bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Melt butter or vegetable oil in hot skillet.
Add meat and stir.
Sear quickly (without browning or burning).
Add onions and fry for 5 minutes.
Add celery, salt, pepper and hot water.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add drained bean sprouts.
Mix thoroughly. Heat to boiling point.
Add flavoring and thickening ingredients. Stir lightly and cook 5 minutes.
Serve piping hot with chow mein noodles or cooked rice.
Serves 2.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together.
Place in pie pan and form to all the edges. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Take out before it browns.

title: cornflake casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: green chili enchilada casserole
directions: Combine soups, sour cream, milk, chilies, onion and salt in saucepan.
Cook until thick (a little).
Layer tortillas, chicken and sauce.
Top with cheese.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients in bowl together.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Crumble corn flakes and mix with melted margarine. Stir and put on top and brown for 5 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms, pat dry and remove stems and chop stems. Combine chopped stems with next 3 ingredients.
Cook sausage until crumbly.
Drain off fat, stir in cheese and mix well.
Spoon into caps and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen, approximately.

title: never fail angel food cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Sift sugar 5 or 6 times.
Put 1/2 of the sugar in the flour and sift 15 times.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until foamy, then add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar and then fold in sugar and flour mixture.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(I use pieces of wax paper for the sifting process.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Coat sides and bottom of casserole dish with margarine.
Put 1/2 of broccoli in bottom of pan and cover with cheese.
Repeat with a second layer.
Crush crackers finely and cover top of casserole.
Cut margarine into 1 inch pats and cover crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts and crackers are lightly toasted.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together ingredients, except for bacon.
Put in baking dish and top with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until sauce is thick and bacon is brown.

title: forbus fajitas
directions: Cut peppers and onion into small strips; place in large skillet with oleo and wine.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring occasionally until wine is almost absorbed and peppers and onions are done.
Add grilled chicken strips to skillet and heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve wrapped in a flour tortilla with sour cream and salsa.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken and bay leaf until done. Cool, skin and debone.
Chop into pieces.
Cook yellow rice with onion.
Add all other ingredients to this.
Add chicken.
Mix all together.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: peas with water chestnuts(microwave)
directions: Place onion, bouillon cubes and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 2 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Add flour to onion.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 1 to 2 minutes, or until thickened.
Add peas, water chestnuts and salt.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 7 to 9 minutes, or until peas are tender.

title: apple harvest squares
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, salt and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in butter until the mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange the apple slices on top of the crumbs; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Now, in a small bowl, combine remaining sugar with the rest of the ingredients.
Spoon over baked apples; bake for another 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Yield about 20 pieces.

title: acorn squash slices with lemon glaze
directions: Wash squash, cut lengthwise, clean and cut into slices.
Put in skillet or pan with water.
Cook until tender.

title: baked squash
directions: Add
soup and chilies to squash, onion and eggs.
Cover bottom of pan with Cheez Whiz and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Heat 1 cup nectar.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining nectar and pineapple, undrained.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add nuts and bananas.
Pour into 1-quart dish and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cider jelly
directions: In a large kettle, heat cider, red hots and pectin, stirring often.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Add sugar.
Return to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Skim off any foam.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 6 half pints.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Slice onion over potatoes.
Then put the can of mushroom soup and chicken over the potatoes and then add or layer the hamburger or steak (browned).
Next cook for 45 minutes at 300° and when it's done, put the two kinds of cheese on top and leave in the oven until melted good.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Fill middle of flour tortilla; roll tortilla and place seam down in baking dish.
Place cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk, making according to directions on box. Make this first.
Crush the Oreos (set aside).
Cream together oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Blend Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Blend in the mixture of oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and cut thick. Combine all ingredients; cover with hot water. Cook until green turns brown. Put in hot jars and seal. If you want to cook some of it, drain it but don't add any more salt. Delicious floured or mealed and fried.

title: chicken vermicelli carbonara
directions: In a wide nonstick frying pan, combine onion, fennel seed and 1 cup of the broth. Bring to a boil.
Boil, stirring occasionally, until liquid has evaporated.
Continue to cook until browned bits accumulate in pan.
Add water, two tablespoons at a time, stirring until all browned bits are loosened. Continue to cook until mixture begins to brown again.
Repeat deglazing, using 2 tablespoons water each time, until onions are a uniformly light golden brown color.

title: mom's never fail pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour/salt mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large measuring cup.
Add to dry ingredients.
Roll on floured surface.
Large recipe; yields 4 or 5 double crust pies.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream and mix together Crisco, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Chill dough.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except the butter or margarine, broccoli and corn muffin mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook the broccoli until nearly done.
Place broccoli in pan. Sprinkle the corn muffin mix over the broccoli.
Pour the melted margarine over the corn muffin mix.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: microwave easy fudge
directions: Place chips in 8 x 8 microwave pan. Melt in microwave 4 minutes on High. Stir in condensed milk, vanilla and water. When chocolate hardens, cut into squares. Yields 30 pieces.

title: strawberry danish
directions: Tear cake in pieces and pack in deep dish with small Cool Whip.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, large Cool Whip
and vanilla. Pour over first layer, mix strawberries and glaze.
Pour over this and refrigerate for several hours.

title: orange pimento salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Cool until syrupy.
Add pineapple and marshmallows. Whip the cream stiff and add cheese spread. Whip until smooth.
Add to jello mixture.
Pour in mold greased with mayonnaise.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring chicken stock to low simmer.
While stock is heating, melt margarine in a separate pan over low flame.
Begin to chop broccoli.
Be sure to discard very end of broccoli stalk, as its woody end is very unappealing to the soup.
Once you have measured out the correct amount of broccoli, place it into simmering stock and allow to cook until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Increase heat under margarine to medium flame and add flour to it, creating your own roux.
The roux needs to be cooked for about 5 to 7 minutes, being stirred constantly with wooden spoon to avoid burning.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: No candy thermometer is needed.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Drain salmon (reserve liquid).
Add milk to liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Add to biscuit mix, along with egg and lemon juice.
Blend in salmon and vegetables; season with salt.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat, at 375°.
Fry until brown on both sides (about 3 minutes).
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Serves 4.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Place crumbled saltine crackers in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Now put a layer of oysters.
Add more crumbled saltine crackers, layer of oysters again.
Sprinkle onion and carrots over oysters.
Next, put crumbled saltines.
Beat eggs. Add milk, water and pepper.
Pour over oysters and saltines in dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Blend in the well beaten eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Put in 2 long rolls and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: nutty-cereal snack
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix first 3 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan.
Heat butter in 1-quart saucepan until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in last 3 ingredients.
Pour over cereal mix and toss until coated.
Bake uncovered.
Stir occasionally for 25 minutes.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Lightly toss all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole. Refrigerate covered.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix together and let stand on counter 8 to 12 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
When rice is done, remove lid and set aside.
Cook meat with 1/4 to 1/2 bacon grease until brown, then add carrots, cabbage (optional celery or others) and onions and fry together.
When done, add catsup and soy sauce, salt and pepper as desired.
Add cooked rice, meat and vegetables and fry together.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, stir together cake mix and gelatin.
Add eggs, cooking oil and wine; beat at low speed of mixer until moistened.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Pour into Pamed Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: quick-easy-good
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cool and skin.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place into 6 x 10-inch baking dish (greased).
Cook Stove Top dressing, following directions on box.
Spoon over chicken bites.
Spread broccoli over dressing.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese (more is better).
Microwave until cheese is melted and heated through, or in oven at 375° until cheese is melted and heated through, about 1/2 hour.

title: bonita marie
directions: Precook bacon in either microwave or regular oven to remove some of the fat, without making it too crisp to roll.
Cut round steak into strips.
Roll a slice of bacon with each strip of round steak and fasten with a toothpick.
Place rolls, side by side, in a covered roaster or casserole dish.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator, then form into 2 balls.
Roll balls in chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated or may freeze. Yields 2 cheese balls.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine corn chowder, frozen corn, milk, salt, pepper and butter in a 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Cover.
Place over low heat; bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer until thoroughly heated. Remove from heat.
Pour into bowls and dust lightly with paprika. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon parsley over bowl of chowder.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger haystack
directions: Brown and season hamburger in skillet.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour tomato soup over meat, place layer of onions, carrots and potatoes on top.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup on top of vegetables and meat.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: four layer delight
directions: Soften oleo.
Press flour, oleo and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese (completely softened) and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on cool crust.
Mix and spread on pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: swiss ham bake
directions: In medium skillet, saute onions and pepper in butter.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
In a 3-quart buttered casserole, layer 1/3 noodles, 1/3 cheese, 1/3 ham and 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers one more time.
The third layer will consist of noodles, ham and cheese only.
Saute bread crumbs in 1/4 cup of butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easiest microwave cocoa fudge
directions: Microwave
powdered
sugar,
cocoa,
milk and butter on High (full
power)
until butter is melted; about 2 or 3 minutes,
stir until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat dough out onto a jelly roll pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In deep frying pan, combine butter, diced onion, and diced tomato.
Saute on high heat until tomato starts to cook down.
Add hot sauce and shrimp and cook until shrimp are pink. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring pan to mild boil and add cornstarch to desired thickness.
Serve mixture over a bed of rice and top with cheese.
Cheese should melt due to temperature of main dish. Serve.

title: kota soupa avegolemeno(chicken rice soup)
directions: Bring chicken stock to boil; add rice, salt and pepper and cook until rice is done.
Remove 1 1/2 cups stock to cool. Beat eggs just until foamy.
Slowly stir in lemon juice and cooled stock.
Add pieces of stewing chicken as desired.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla.
Mix in flour; add nuts.
Roll into small rolls or wafers.
Place on cookie sheets and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat until blended.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: baked turbot
directions: Place frozen fillet of turbot in shallow baking dish.
Dot with pats of margarine (do not use butter).
Salt lightly.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger with onions.
Chop as you fry to make crumbly mixture.
Drain then add rest of ingredients; serve on warm buns.

title: junk yard salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chicken ole
directions: Combine taco sauce, mustard and lime juice in large bowl.

Add chicken, turning to coat. Cover; marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat until foamy. Remove chicken from marinade; reserve marinade. Add chicken to skillet; cook 10 minutes, until brown on both sides. Add marinade; cook 5 minutes until chicken is glazed from marinade. Place chicken on platter. Boil marinade and pour over chicken. Garnish with sour cream and parsley.

title: ziti sauce
directions: Cook spices, onion and chopped meat until brown, then add tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with Italian sweet sausage and/or meatballs.
Serve over ziti and with a salad to make a complete meal.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit.
Cut up bananas and apples.
Mix together. Fold in whipped cream.

title: cold buffet rice dish
directions: Saute parsley, onions and peppers until soft, but not brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss all together and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and water.
Stir next 3 ingredients until mixed.
Mix with Jell-O and chill.

title: mercury's melting moments cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased pan.
Press with fork.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry mixture and beat well.

title: veggie bars
directions: Pat out rolls in a large cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or slightly brown.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing.
Chop all vegetables. Save a few to put on top. Mix vegetables with cream cheese mixture and spread on rolls. Sprinkle with remaining vegetables and grated cheese. Cut in bars. Refrigerate.

title: toffee
directions: Melt butter on low; stir in sugar and remove from heat.
Stir until butter and sugar are completely mixed (no butter should be floating on top), approximately 5 minutes.
Add Karo and water and return to heat.
Cook until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 295°.
Add chopped pecans and turn onto buttered cookie sheet.
As it cools, run spatula under candy to prevent sticking. When candy is pretty hard, spread 1/2 of chocolate on one side and sprinkle with 1/2 of ground pecans. Repeat with other side.
When chocolate is completely dry, break candy into pieces. It should be stored in a cool place.
Can be frozen.

title: easy 3-minute white sauce
directions: To skim milk, add all ingredients and beat with electric mixer until well mixed.
Cook in a heavy pan over moderate heat, stirring constantly to prevent mixture from sticking.
Sauce will be thick and smooth in 2 to 4 minutes, almost fluffy in texture. Makes 2 cups.
Contains 79 calories per cup.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in medium saucepan until thick (like cooked cereal).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, then eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Knead well on lightly floured surface.
Place in bowl; cover and let rise.
Punch down. Roll out to 1-inch thickness; cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Brush with melted butter; dust with cornmeal.
Place on greased cookie sheet; cover and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. (Dough will keep in refrigerator for several days.)
Yield:
18 rolls.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring mustard seed, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over other ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer fruit in 4 1/2-quart casserole. Scatter raisins and almonds over fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place brandy and lemon juice in cup measure.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Pour over fruit.
Add enough reserved fruit juice to just cover fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pear honey(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Wash, peel and core fruit.
Put pears through a food chopper using coarse blade.
Mix all ingredients and heat, stirring thoroughly until sugar is dissolved.
Boil mixture until it is thick and clear, about 10 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add grated cheese on top of all the meat.
Be generous with the cheese.
Add 1 1/4 cups milk to can of mushroom soup and pour over the cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrotslincoln, nebraska
directions: Bring to a boil and add carrots, onion and green peppers:
1 can tomato soup, 1 tsp. prepared mustard, 1 c. sugar, 1
tsp. Worchester sauce, 3/4 c. white vinegar, 1/2 c. salad
oil and salt and pepper to taste.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix pie filling and thoroughly drained pineapple well.
Mix condensed milk with mixture and then fold in Cool Whip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer boiled chicken, cream of chicken, cream of celery and Veg-All.
Mix together margarine, milk and flour for crust.
Crust will have the same consistency of pancake batter; pour over top. Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: fruit and cereal brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cereal and orange juice in bowl.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Mix in oil, egg and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except topping.
Pour into pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Sprinkle topping over cake.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Take a large 5 to 7 pound beef brisket (the best, rump, round, or like roast).
Place in a pan lined with heavy foil.
Sprinkle with onion salt, garlic salt and celery salt.
Pour on 1/2 to 3/4 bottle of Wrights liquid smoke.
Wrap foil tightly around roast. Place into 250° oven for 6 to 8 hours.
Uncover and top with any good bottled barbecue sauce.
Bake for another 40 minutes, uncovered.
Can be served hot or cold.
Slice or shred.
I shred mine when cool and freeze in plastic bags.
Delicious!

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt peanut morsels until smooth over low heat, set aside. In large bowl, combine butter and sugar, beat well.
Blend in melted morsels.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Pour in greased and floured pan. Bake 35-40 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Place grated zucchini in a colander and squeeze out as much moisture as possible with hands or back of wooden spoon; set aside.
In a large bowl combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, zucchini and onion; mix until combined.
Preheat griddle; grease if necessary.
Using 1/4 cup batter for each, pour onto griddle and flatten slightly to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes until golden, turn and cook other side.
Makes 10, 65 calories each.

title: hot wings
directions: Melt butter with hot sauce in microwave.
Place wings in pan. Pour sauce mixture over wings.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bake to death at 350° for 2 or more hours, basting occasionally.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In skillet (over medium heat) place salad oil; add onions and cook 2 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cup water, soy sauce and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water and slowly stir into onions until sauce thickens.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook until tender, then strain.
Double if needed.

title: punky's lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Beat in sugar, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Pour in shell.
Cut butter into pieces and lay on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until puffed and slightly golden brown. Cool slightly.

title: cranberry warmer
directions: In 4-cup glass measure, mix all ingredients.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Strain and pour into serving cups.

title: homestyle spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or pot, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 6 cups.

title: "granny smith" apple dip
directions: Soak apples overnight in the pineapple juice.
Combine cream cheese, brown sugar, vanilla and Heath Bits to make a stiff dip.

title: white chocolate fondue
directions: Heat eagle brand milk and 1/2 c milk in a small saucepan until mixture is creamy. Add white chocolate chopped, stir until completely melted. Serve warm. Great with fresh fruit, pretzels, and cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, beginning with flour and ending with flour, to creamed mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 320°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix everything.
Bake in long dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: alpine pie
directions: Soften yogurt in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Combine dates, pecans, gingersnaps, coconut and maple syrup.
Mix well. Fill pie crust with half the yogurt. Slice banana and arrange evenly over yogurt.
Spread date mixture over banana. Top with remaining yogurt.
Freeze until ready to serve (at least 2 hours).

title: fruit and nut tropical slaw
directions: Drain pineapple; save 2 teaspoons juice.
Combine juice with lemon juice.
Mix; set aside.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to hamburger mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with 3 cups instant mashed potatoes. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups grated cheese if desired.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: miniature fruitcakes
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, all-purpose flour, baking powder, salt, walnuts, dates and candied fruit.
Combine egg yolks and vanilla;
stir into dry ingredients.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Fill greased and floured muffin cups two-thirds full.
Cover the muffin tins tightly with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Uncover; top each fruitcake with cherries.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 5 minutes.
Run a knife around the edges of each cup; remove to a wire rake to cool completely.
Yields:
1 dozen.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add chili mix, enchilada mix, tomato sauce, water and Accent.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Put a little of sauce on bottom of 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Place 2 tortillas on sauce; add more sauce and sprinkle cheese (both kinds) on sauce.
Repeat layer, ending with cheese.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven until bubbly and cheese melted.

title: california vegetable medley
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in microwave or double boiler.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the next 2 ingredients.
Pour sauce over frozen vegetables.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Mix stuffing mix and put on baked casserole; continue baking for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti and beef bake
directions: Cook spaghetti, using package directions; drain.
Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring frequently; drain.
Reserve 1 cup shredded cheese.
Combine remaining cheese, hot spaghetti, hot ground beef mixture, undrained tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper in bowl; mix until cheese is melted.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with reserved cheese; dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
May freeze before baking.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Tear bread into pieces and cover the bottom of dish.
Break sausage into pieces; spread over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Pour mixture of milk, eggs, salt, pepper and mustard (if preferred) over the ingredients already in pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
This is good warmed over.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix over pineapple and mix well.
Pour remaining ingredients in and stir thoroughly.
Pour into oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put these all together.
Pour dressing over about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: sauteed cabbage
directions: Dice bacon and brown in 2-quart pot.
Peel and dice onion, add to rendered bacon in pot.
Slice smoked sausage and add to bacon and onion.
Cook approximately 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Quarter cabbage, pull apart and add to pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pot and cook on medium heat until tender.
Do not add water and do not overcook.

title: broccoli puff(healthy diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole or 5 1/2-cup souffle dish with cooking spray.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Beat baking mix, milk, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into dish/casserole.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato skins
directions: Clean potatoes; prick with fork.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cut each potato lengthwise into quarters.
Scoop out insides, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells. (Reserve pulp for another use.)

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in gradually the milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat. Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish. Cover with topping. Bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sugar oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix, roll and cut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Egg do better when beaten separately, then added to creamed mixture.
The cake will rise higher.
Sift in the 2 kinds of flour.
Add milk, alternating flour and milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in tube pan.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well. Make a hole in the middle. Add soda, milk and lard. Work together until stiff. Put on floured board; knead with a little flour until it can be rolled out. Cut with biscuit cutter. Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick. Bake in hot oven about 400°.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: In a cup, place the yeast and warm water. Set aside.
Then in a large bowl, mix margarine, buttermilk and sugar.
Slowly add the yeast and water. Stir, then add the flour.
Form into a ball after kneading it for about 5 minutes.
Place somewhere warm and let set for it to rise. Cut into your biscuits and bake in a 450° oven for at least 10 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: country lemon tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Prepare crust.
While crust is baking, prepare filling.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with enough buttered crumbs or croutons to cover casserole.
Bake in oven about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: california dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until creamy.
Serve with fresh vegetables, chips or crackers.
Yield:
1 pint (2 cups). Protein 4 g, fat 2 g, calories per serving 43.
Two tablespoons = 1/2 meat, medium fat exchange.

title: peasant rye
directions: Hollow out whole rye loaf.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into the hole.
Chop up the rest of the loaf to dip.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; mix well. Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Cook in hot oil over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned. Drain on paper towels.

title: wine cake
directions: *If using large package of pudding, add about 1/2 cup water.

title: fabulous italian breadsticks
directions: Press out bread dough to fill greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Brush with olive oil.
Sprinkle with basil and thyme.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until light brown. Cut into 1 x 4-inch strips.
Serve with spaghetti sauce.

title: asparagus dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers, chips or vegetable dippers.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add soup and remaining ingredients plus 2 cans of water or to your desired consistency.
Season to taste. Simmer until done.
Serve with toasted French bread.
This is good on a cold night and doesn't take as long as regular stew.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add whipped cream and mix well.
Fold in drained pineapple. Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers and fill with mixture.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Mold into balls a little smaller than a golf ball.
Chill thoroughly.
Dip in beaten egg, then roll in fine bread crumbs. Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: olive spread
directions: Mix and spread on bread for finger sandwiches.

title: english cottage pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Place in casserole pan.
Prepare gravy mix according to package directions and pour over meat mixture.
Spread mashed potato mixture over meat.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar with cream cheese. Add thawed strawberries, including juice. Add drained pineapple, bananas and chopped pecans. Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in 9 x 9 pan. Cut into squares and serve slightly thawed.

title: dianne's creamed crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside. Cream margarine and gradually add sugars.
Beat until light.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Use ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup measure to drop dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until firm).
One cup of raisins can be substituted.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar, flour, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add 7-Up, beating again. Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: While broccoli is cooking, combine all other ingredients. Place in a greased casserole dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs and top with 1/2 stick butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown and bubbling.

title: sugar-free pineapple muffins
directions: Beat butter, eggs, pineapple juice and lemon juice in bowl. Add flour, baking soda and baking powder, stirring until moistened.
Stir in pineapple.
Spoon into greased and floured muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Debone and dice chicken.
Save stock and cook fettucine (following directions on package).
Drain cooked fettuccine and pour cold water over the fettucine so that the spaghetti will not get any softer. Drain fettucine and and pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: grandma's rolls and bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water water. Scald milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Let cool to lukewarm. Pour milk mixture, yeast and water into flour and add eggs. Knead bread about 10 minutes. Let raise to double. Knead again. Let raise to double. Make bread or cinnamon rolls.

title: little joes
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet; add onion and cook over medium heat until soft.
Add the beef, mixing with the onion and breaking it up into small bits with a fork.
Cook until redness is gone (drain at this point if needed).
Add spinach and mix well. Stir and cook for 3 to 4 minutes, then salt to taste.
Mix a dash or so of Tabasco with the eggs, then pour over beef mixture and stir until the eggs are set.
Remove from heat and put on a warm platter.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over.
Sprinkle with rice or noodles.

title: green bean vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
(Drain beans and corn.)
Do not add water to the soup before adding.
Top with 1/2 stick margarine and soda cracker crumbs, mixed together.
Spread over top.
Spread 1/2 cup slivered almonds over the crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese, Corn Flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter. Spread into greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over mixture. Crush Corn Flakes and combine with melted butter. Put this on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf, world's greatest
directions: Beat egg lightly in medium bowl. Add Accent, salt, pepper, basil, thyme, ketchup, mustard and bread crumbs. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Add to bowl and mix. Add celery, onions and cheese. Add ground beef and mix (12 x 5 loaf). Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add vinegar, oregano and fresh ground pepper to taste.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
It is also good if you add slices of avocados and tomatoes.

title: coconut peaks
directions: While margarine is hot, stir in sifted icing sugar, canned milk and coconut.
Make in drops and drop on top of coconut peaks the melted bits and butter.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put pineapple in bottom of pan evenly.
Pour cherry filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over the mixture.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Add finely cut-up margarine over top.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well. Add flour, 1 cup at a time, baking powder and milk. Mix together well. Bake in a 350° oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: In medium glass bowl, layer 1/2 each of the chicken, water chestnuts, sprouts and onion rings.
Pour half of the dressing over the top and season with pepper.
Repeat each layer, beginning with chicken and ending with dressing and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Serve cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika.
Using high heat, brown meat in butter on all sides.
Reduce heat.
Add wine, soy sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat.
Arrange onion, green peppers and tomatoes over steak.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes more. Serve over beds of hot rice.
(I usually make extra sauce for serving with rice.)

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling, salted water (for 10 minutes).
Cut in halves and scoop out centers.
Mix pulp with remaining ingredients.
Fill zucchini.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve with bacon for six.

title: recipe for living
directions: Take the patience, love, generosity, laughter and understanding and sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith and mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve to everyone you meet.

title: tortellini spinach salad(ready in 15 minutes or less)
directions: In a salad bowl, combine the spinach, tortellini and parmesan cheese. Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat.

title: peanut butter chicken breasts
directions: Saute onion and add garlic. Remove to serving platter.
Saute chicken until golden on both sides.
Replace with onion mix.
Add broth, seasonings and peanut butter.
Whisk until hot and smooth. Add chicken, cover tightly and simmer 30 minutes, turning chicken once.
Serve with Spatzle (chunky little German noodles).
Serves 4.

title: hearty italian soup
directions: Precook hot sausage; crumble.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot and let simmer 6 to 8 hours.
Can add other vegetables your family likes.

title: iceberg and avocado aspic salad(makes 8 to 12 servings)
directions: Hollow inside of lettuce.
Thoroughly mix all other ingredients and stuff tight in lettuce head.
Wrap in Saran Wrap. Chill overnight.
Serve in narrow wedges topping with French dressing.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Remove.
Season with salt and pepper. Saute onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add meat, tomato sauce, bay leaf and basil.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender. Serve over rice and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: vacation bible school famous pretzels
directions: In a large bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and sugar. Blend in the flour.
Knead until well blended, smooth and elastic. Roll the dough flat and cut into strips 1/2-inch wide.
Form the dough into shapes and put on greased baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse pretzel salt.
(Use margarita salt if you can't find pretzel salt.)
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Whisk sour cream, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons whipping cream.
Add peanut butter and whisk until smooth.
Spoon into pie crust and freeze 3 hours.

title: chicken provolone
directions: Between 2 pieces of Saran Wrap, pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
In a small bowl, mix flour, salt, pepper and tarragon. Add chicken and dredge to coat.
In a large skillet, melt butter. Add chicken and saute, turning once, until fork-tender.
Add wine and turn to coat.
Remove to a shallow pan and keep warm.
Add mushrooms to a skillet; saute 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Top each chicken piece with 2 tablespoons mushrooms, sauce and 1 slice of cheese.
Broil 8 inches from heat until cheese melts.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams and add bottle of shrimp sauce.
Roll cream cheese into a ball.
Pour sauce mix over cheese ball.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cap'n crunch balls
directions: Heat until it bubbles.
Mix in peanut butter; add cereal. Form into balls or drop by spoonful.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare salad as you like it;
include carrots, cheese, tomato, cauliflower, broccoli, cucumber, etc.

title: three bean bake
directions: Brown bacon, onion and celery in pan.
Drain off fat.
Add to remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and put in baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake at least 1 hour at 300°.

title: punch
directions: Make lemons into lemonade, then add all juices.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve. Chill.
Can be served with ice.

title: almond casserole
directions: Bring
water
and
soup
to
boil.
Add rice and reduce heat. Simmer
for 25 minutes until water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Fry sausage until brown.
Remove from pan and pour off as much fat as possible.
Add celery, onions and pepper to a
little fat and brown gently.
Add rice, sausage and 1/2 cup almonds together;
mix
well in a 2-quart dish.
Garnish with rest of almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir egg yolks into milk.
Add juice and rind.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and broil in 300° oven. Cool.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: cape cod clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 2 cups; set aside.
In a large saucepan, fry salt pork or bacon until crisp; remove bits of pork or bacon and set aside.
Add reserved liquid, potatoes and onion to fat in saucepan.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in clams, 2 cups of the milk and the light cream. Stir remaining 1/2 cup milk into flour; stir into chowder.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Add Worcestershire, 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Sprinkle pork or bacon atop.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Place pineapple in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring.
Stir in buttermilk, coconut and pecans.
Cool.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken wings
directions: Rinse wings; split each into 2 pieces.
Mix all other ingredients (except cornstarch and water) in a bowl.
Lay chicken wings in a baking dish and pour mixture over them.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: In a medium size bowl
put the egg yolks and beat until a light lemon color,
add lemon juice and lemon rind and stir until completely mixed; stir in sweetened condensed milk and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a baked and cooled graham cracker crust. Top with your favorite meringue and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Keep refrigerated after it cools.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Saute chicken after coating with flour mixture.
Remove from pan.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, ginger, lemon juice and cornstarch and put in pan.
Simmer until liquid thickens.
Put chicken back into pan and simmer with top off 20 minutes.
Add pineapple.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together salt, Worcestershire sauce, oil, sugar, catsup and vinegar.
Warm up.
Wash spinach and tear up into bite-size pieces.
Drain water chestnuts and bean sprouts; add to spinach. Add onion, eggs and mushrooms.
Fry bacon.
Add to spinach.
Pour warm dressing over spinach.

title: cindy's cheese bread
directions: Melt oleo.
Add poppy seed and garlic.
Slice bread; butter with mixture.
Put a slice of cheese.
Repeat until end of loaf. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Spray with cooking spray or grease with margarine.
Place a layer of saltines in bottom of pan.
Simmer butter and brown sugar until they form a clear brown syrup.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers.
Spread the chocolate to cover toffee and sprinkle pecans over it.
Chill and break into pieces.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
(You can use cranberries, apples or dates, if desired.)
Grease muffin tin well with butter.
Fill to top of cup; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen large muffins.

title: children's favorite cake pudding
directions: Place ingredients in small jar, leaving half of jar empty for shaking purposes.
Secure lid.
Shake for a few minutes.
Ready to eat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in margarine in a 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown.
Add flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Stir in soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through. Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Crush potato chips until very fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Grease baking dish with butter.
Spread in mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top starts to brown.

title: seafood jambalaya
directions: Cut peppers, onions and celery into 1-inch pieces. Steam or parboil celery in picante juice.
Add peppers and onions and cook until crunchy. Saute scallops and shrimp. Saute mushrooms separately. Mix all ingredients together and cook for just 10 minutes on medium heat. Serve with rice.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery and okra in bacon grease.
Add tomatoes and simmer.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil rolled out dough on one side, 2 minutes and 7-inches from heat.
Turn, brush with olive oil and broil 2 minutes more.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute pepper, onion, parsley, thyme and bay leaf in margarine until tender; do not brown.
Add tomatoes, pumpkin, water and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears.
Heat juice to boiling point.
Add gelatin; stir until completely dissolved.
Beat cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Slowly add hot gelatin to cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until thick and beginning to set.
Mash pears with fork; fold into thickened mixture, along with Cool Whip, pecans and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate to set.

title: harvest loaf cake(pumpkin bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine flour with soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter and add sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin. Add chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool loaf, then glaze.
Loaf is usually done in about 1 hour.

title: grandma's success cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and soda.
Add vinegar, flour and vanilla. By hand fold in 1 cup Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute 1 large onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli for a few minutes.
Drain. Combine all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Bring 1 cup cranberry juice to a boil in saucepan.
Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in chilled cranberry juice. Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into greased ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold into serving plate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: gram's apple pie
directions: Sprinkle in bottom of pie shell:
1 tablespoon flour, 2 tablespoons cinnamon and white sugar mixture, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 apples slices.
Then repeat.
Seal with top crust. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fannie's coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks; add sugar, flour, vanilla, salt and vinegar.
Pour milk into saucepan. Add coconut and margarine.
Heat on medium until margarine melts. Cool slightly until pouring into beaten mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 30 minutes until firm.
Top with meringue and bake until golden brown.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, soup, margarine, mayonnaise and onion.
Pour over broccoli; sprinkle cheese over top.
Pour crumbs on top, pressing down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bring squash and onions to a boil for 15 minutes. Drain. Blend together cream of chicken soup, milk, cornbread and butter and mix with squash/onions.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle top with grated cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/4 cup of juice.
Put salmon in mixing bowl and add the egg.
Mix well and then add 1/2 cup flour. Add salt to taste.
Add baking powder to reserved juice and beat until foamy.
Use large cup for this as it will increase in volume.
Add salmon mixture and mix well.

title: chocolate peanut butter muffins
directions: You will need 2 mini muffin pans.

title: chocolate toffee cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until well-blended. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Stir in 1 2/3 c. chip mixture. Pour into crust(s). Bake 10 minutes, reduce heat to 250° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until set. Do not open oven door in between temperature change. Cool on wire rack and then refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: pantry shelf paella
directions: Brown chicken in butter or oil.
Cook until almost done. Remove.
Add onion and rice.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine tomato paste and water.
Add to rice with shrimp, salt, garlic powder and cayenne.
Stir in garbanzo beans and their liquid and peas if desired.
Return chicken to the pot.
Cover, simmer and cook 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar. Mix in egg yolk and flour. Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Dissolve coffee in a gallon of boiling water.
Add sugar and chill overnight.
When ready to serve, add the vanilla and milk. Put ice cream in a punch bowl and pour coffee mixture over it. Serves 40 or more.

title: pound cake squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Mix until well blended. Spread the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ground beef and vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onions in small amount of fat; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in large kettle.
Add beef and onions. Simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried apples
directions: Put apples in frying pan (do not peel).
Add sugar and butter. Fry apples until sticky.

title: mable's orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; cream well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, add to creamed mixture.
Mix
orange
slices, dates, nuts and coconut with flour, coating all
pieces.
Add flour mixture to creamed ingredients, mixing well.
Bake
in
greased
and floured tube pan at 250° for approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: play doh
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put food coloring in oil and water mixture.
You can also put peppermint extract or other for a nice smell.
Over medium heat, cook entire mixture about 5 minutes or until it sticks together in a big ball.
Remove from heat.
Using your hands, squeeze and knead until soft and smooth.
It will last a long time in an airtight container.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter. Bake on cookie sheet approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well in the middle.
Pour remaining ingredients into the hollow.
Mix with a large spoon until smooth.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
