Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.
Cool slightly in pan and turn onto rack.
(Freezes well.)

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix and leave out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours before using.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth and doughy.
Divide mixture in half; add a few drops of the different extracts to each half.
Taste and adjust flavor if needed.
Blend green food coloring in the wintergreen and red food coloring in the peppermint, just a few drops at a time.
Pinch off small pieces and roll in sugar and press into mold or leave in circles. Refrigerate, covered.

title: melon - lime beverage
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Pour into 4 tall glasses. Garnish with a slice of lime or melon ball kabob.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine nuts in bottom of pan.
In a large bowl, put cake and pudding mixes.
Add rum extract, oil, water and eggs.
Mix for 2 minutes. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove and pour on hot Rum Glaze.

title: aunt winkie's breakfast casserole
directions: Mix sausage, bread, eggs, milk, soup and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350° the next morning (until bubbly).

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray muffin cups with a vegetable oil spray and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Freezes well.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: iowa corn and sausage casserole
directions: Partially cook sausage; drain.
Blend in eggs and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 1/4 cup crumbs.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: ruby's buttermilk
directions: Stir up in a glass gallon jug.
Let sit out until it clabbers. Stir and put in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Pull off bone.
Add chicken and all other ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Pat dry.
Separate caps from stems (stems are used in the filling).
Brush caps with oil.
Saut stems and onions.
Set aside to cool.

title: savannah red rice
directions: In large skillet fry bacon until crisp.
Add onions and peppers; fry until brown.
Add rice, tomatoes and Tabasco.
Stir. Add meat, salt and pepper.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: southwest corn bake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a greased baking dish.
Add cheese and chilies on mixture.
Top with remaining mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove the lid the last 15 minutes.

title: pizza-fast dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar in a bowl, then mix in all of the other ingredients.
Beat vigorously.
Dough will be soft.
Rub a little oil in a bowl.
Place on lightly floured bread board; knead slightly.
Let dough rest for approximately 10 minutes on the bread board.
Roll into pizza pan or cookie sheet rubbed with oil.
May let dough rise on cookie sheet.
Place all of the ingredients wanted on the pizza; bake until done.
Use cooked sausage or cooked hamburger for the meat portion.

title: tostadas
directions: Fry day old tortillas in a little hot oil or heat on ungreased fry pan.
Drain on paper.
Spread beans then top with other ingredients.
Sprinkle Tabasco sauce or Mexican salsa.
Serve as a snack or meal.
Enjoy.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine Jell-O packages in hot water. Mix until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into a casserole dish. Refrigerate until set.

title: rice casserole #1
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients together in a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: lo-cal banana nut bread
directions: Combine eggs, milk, flavorings, sweeteners and baking powder in bowl and beat with electric hand mixer until stiff as can be.
Add sliced bananas and grits; beat well with mixer (this fluffs it up). Pour into loaf pan, muffin pan or whatever that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.
One serving equals 1 egg (protein), 1 bread and 1 milk.

title: choc-no bake cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan the salt, cocoa, sugar, milk and oleo. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Then fold in oatmeal. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese together and form into a flat round.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Surround with crackers and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash well.
Mix all ingredients with potatoes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with topping and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in butter about 20 minutes.
Cover the pot; stir occasionally.
Add flour and cook 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add parsley and shrimp.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Stir frequently (shrimp about 15 minutes).
Add half and half cream; cook very slowly.
Add half of the Velveeta cheese and pepper.
Cook over low heat about 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Season to taste.
While shrimp is cooking, boil the noodles.
Add cooked noodles to shrimp.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish (glass).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with remaining Velveeta cheese (cut in little, thin slices).
Put in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger corn bake
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Stir in corn (drained), cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in small noodles, cooked and drained. Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Cut up and brown chicken in fat and put aside.
Using a clean pan, brown onions, pepper and garlic in bread.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; cook for 10 minutes.
Place chicken in casserole and pour in sauce, adding fat in which chicken was browned.
Cover with brown paper and lid; bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. When ready to serve, add blanched and browned almonds and well-washed currants.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix together butter, onion, mustard, seeds, seasoning and lemon juice.
Slice bread but leave bottom intact.
Put slices of cheese in each cut of bread.
Slice opposite direction so you have small squares.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread butter mixture over top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cheese should be melted and bread should be golden.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole combine butter and onion.
Microwave at High for 1 to 2 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes, or until thickened, stirring after first 2 minutes and then after every minute.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Add to thickened sauce.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 10 to 15 minutes, or until potatoes are fork-tender, stirring every 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Cut up chicken and put in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Add onion, bay leaves, salt, peppercorns and celery with leaves.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Strain liquid and refrigerate until fat comes to top; take off fat.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown beef on both sides in skillet.
Place in roasted pan. Cook 25 minutes for each pound.
Last 1/2 hour add potatoes and carrots.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Do not beat.
Turn into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour; test for doneness. This cake is better if it can stand overnight for flavors to blend.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers. Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Delicious topped with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and sour cream.

title: festive banana and sweet potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, mash sweet potatoes. Add milk and beat until smooth. Beat in salt, nutmeg and pepper. Spread 1/2 of the mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole. Cut bananas in 1 inch chunks and coat with lemon juice. Arrange 1/2 of the bananas over the potatoes in the casserole; top with remaining potato mixture and bananas. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: potato salad
directions: Slice and cook potatoes with skin on; drain.
Add Italian dressing; chill.
Carefully stir the celery and onions into chilled potatoes.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and cucumber salad dressing.
Stir and pour on potatoes.

title: peanutty chocolate snack squares
directions: Line bottom of an 8-inch square pan with graham cracker squares, cutting to fit as necessary.
In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave at High (100%), stirring every 2 minutes, until mixture boils; boil 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips, peanut butter and peanuts. Pour over crackers; spread carefully.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 16 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in baking pan.
Top with crushed Rice Krispies.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: spinach balls
directions: Precook and drain spinach real good.
Mix all of the ingredients and chill.
After chilled, roll into balls and quick freeze on trays in freezer.
Store in freezer bags or plastic containers.
Bring out and bake 15 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place in dish, alternating chicken and dressing with soup and chicken broth. Sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together crackers and margarine with fork.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix pudding and milk with mixer until smooth.
Add ice cream.
Beat until creamy.
Spread on top of Ritz crackers.
Refrigerate and let set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining crackers.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Combine pineapple and apricot nectar in a
saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten eggs.
Fold in carrots, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into an oiled 5 cup jello mold or 9-inch pan.

title: frozen hot cocoa
directions: In large saucepan, combine cocoa, sugar and coffee. Add just enough milk to blend into a smooth paste. Add remaining milk and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Pour mixture into ice cube trays or 2 shallow pans; cover with plastic wrap and freeze at least 8 hours or overnight. Thaw mixture for 5 to 10 minutes; break into chunks. Place in food processor and blend until smooth. Re-freeze at least 4 hours. Break into chunks and serve in dishes with whipped cream and shaved chocolate, if desired. Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: quick salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased casserole loaf pan for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: m-m-m goodies
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil exactly 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Spread on graham crackers, working quickly.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into quarters.
Makes a bunch.

title: skillet corn
directions: Lightly fry beef and onion in butter until beef begins to curl.
Stir in flour.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring, until thickened. Add corn and heat.
Add cheese and mango.
Stir on low heat just until cheese melts.
Serve at once on buttered toast.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: squash-apple casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Combine with brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts and salt.
Alternate layers of squash and apples.
Drizzle each with butter mixture.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
May also be baked in microwave oven.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix oleo and flour; add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Saute celery same way.
Heat broth.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add broth and mix well.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scramble burgers
directions: Cook hamburger, ketchup, mustard and onion.
Mix and add pickle juice and Worcestershire.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Sift flour over mixture and cook 15 minutes more; stir often.
Feeds 15.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Steep the cloves and cinnamon in 1 pint of water.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Slice carrots crosswise at angle, about 1-inch thick.
Cover and cook in boiling water about 5 minutes, until just tender.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger, orange juice and oleo.
Pour over carrots.
Cook slowly about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: carol's pork chop casserole
directions: Roll pork chops in flour; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown pork chops and place in a glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with onions and rice.
Combine cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour over pork chops and rice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until rice is done.
(Ovens may vary.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice peeled apples in 10-inch pie dish and sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice and water.
Mix together sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Pat lightly over apples and bake uncovered at 350° about 1 hour or until fruit is tender and top is lightly browned.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Thinly slice cucumber; sprinkle with salt and let stand while preparing the dressing.
Combine yogurt or sour cream, vinegar, mint, dill and pepper.
Drain cucumber and pour dressing over. Mix well.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: ma neeley's biscuit pudding
directions: Slice or crumble biscuit in baking dish.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour over biscuit.
Bake. If mixture does not cover biscuit, add more milk.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
In large skillet, brown sausage. Remove sausage and pour off half accumulated grease.
Add butter, onions, celery, garlic and chives and saute until soft.
In a blender, blend chicken livers and blend until liquified.
Pour into skillet; cook until done (will change color).
Mix sausage and livers with rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and hot sauce to taste.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken and vegetable sin well-greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Melt butter, add flour, salt and pepper to season. Add chicken stock.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour over vegetables and top with pie crust.
Slit top, press edges.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper penny carrots(yields 8 servings)
directions: Cook sliced carrots until just tender.
Combine onion, bell pepper, soup, sugar substitute, oil, vinegar and seasonings.
Stir until mixed.
Stir in cooked drained carrots.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving.
Will keep for two weeks.

title: party rolls
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed together.
As a loaf cut rolls in 1/2.
Spread mixture.
Place ham and cheese cut apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator coconut cake
directions: Cook white cake mix according to directions.
Cook in 9-inch sheet cake pan.
Cook milk and sugar.
Let boil for about 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
While cake is still hot, punch holes with toothpick in top, then pour hot mixture over top.
Allow to cool. Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle coconut evenly on top and refrigerate.
Lasts for several days.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt.
Crumble until the size of small peas.
Add vinegar, egg and water (small amount at a time). Knead and roll out.
Make 4 pie shells.
May freeze.

title: golden crumb broccoli casserole
directions: In covered saucepan, cook broccoli in small amount of boiling, salted water until barely tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, pimiento, cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian style steak sandwich
directions: Brown onions in butter or margarine until golden brown; remove from pan.
Cut chip steak in small pieces and brown in same pan. Remove steak and place with onions.
Add 1/2 cup water to pan drippings to make broth.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Stir; bring to boil.
Stir in onions and steak. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes until thickened. Top sandwiches with cheese and place in warm oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 large sandwiches or subs.

title: crumb cake
directions: Butter and flour 2 pans, 12 1/8 x 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch size or as close to the size as possible.
Bake cake for about 17 minutes.

title: nothing cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour and soda and add alternately with pineapple.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hot crabmeat
directions: Soften cream cheese with the milk.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread pecans and coconut in bottom of sheet pan.
Mix until creamy cream cheese, margarine, sugar and milk.
Set aside.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour cake mix on top of pecans and coconut.
Drop cream cheese mixture on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana muffins(they will love them for breakfast)
directions: On a piece of wax paper, combine flour, sugar and yeast.
In a saucepan, combine water, milk and margarine until warm.
In a small bowl, beat (electric) eggs and add flavorings.
Remove 3/4 of dry ingredients and add pan mixture; mix in a large bowl.
Add eggs and rest of flour.
Add additional flour as needed.

title: quick bernaise sauce for salmon(for two)
directions: To warm water add Hollandaise sauce (use a fork to blend in the powder).
Bring slowly to a simmer, stirring until the sauce thickens; use a "Dover" beater to smooth it if necessary.
Add a teaspoon of dried tarragon, stirring.
Just before serving, add an equal volume of sour cream, stirring.
This may be used as a hot or cold sauce.

title: toronto french onion soup
directions: In 3 to 4-quart pot, saute onions in 1/4 cup butter until onion slices are limp.
Add more butter if needed to keep from sticking.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, garlic and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until mixture turns golden brown.
Stir in parsley, thyme, beef stock and white wine.
Stir in cognac or brandy.
Toast French bread slices.
Pour soup into six ovenproof bowls and place French bread slices on top of soup.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: english cherubs
directions: Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, butter, flour and dash of salt in a medium mixing bowl; mix until well combined (mixture will look dry).
Press in bottom of a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add beaten egg and mix until crumbs are formed.
Wash fruit and drain.
Fill pan and top with crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: thanksgiving cornbread(easy)
directions: Mix cornmeal, flours, maple syrup, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, egg and milk.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8. Easy for children to make.

title: pork cake
directions: Mix raisins, nuts and allspice together with flour in one bowl.
Put soda in boiling water and pour over pork fat and let stand about 5 minutes.
Add brown sugar and egg and stir until mixed.
Gradually add dry ingredients (raisins, nuts, flour and allspice) until mixed smoothly.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 300° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta biscuit bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in oven in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish or nonaluminum baking pan.
Tilt to evenly coat pan.
Separate dough into 13 biscuits; cut each biscuit into eighths.
Place biscuit pieces in large bowl; toss with 1 3/4 cups salsa.
Spoon evenly into margarine coated pan.
Sprinkle with cheese, bell pepper, onions and ripe olives.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until edges are deep golden brown and center is set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve with 1 cup salsa.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Let milk and vinegar set for 10 minutes and then beat together.
Mix together all ingredients except first two (zucchini and chocolate chips).
Add zucchini and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top of cake.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into shortening mixture.
Let stand a few minutes before rolling out.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook twist macaroni while cooking; brown ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper.
When done, mix macaroni and ground beef together.
Add pizza sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce, sugar, garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in large baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining mixture and another layer of cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Put pepperoni slices on top.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.
Perfect amount for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: choctaw chuck
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Saute beef and onions; drain. Crunch Doritos; cover bottom of casserole dish about 1-inch. Layer beef, beans, mushroom/milk mixed, Ro-Tel, olives and cheese. Bake until bubbly, approximately 20 minutes.

title: crisp chocolate raisin bars(makes 8 servings)
directions: Line 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pan with wax paper. Allow paper to overlap on the sides.

title: soda cracker cake
directions: Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Place in a greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping (Dream Whip) and add fruit topping (use your imagination).
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large saucepot, mix together oil, tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Let simmer.
In skillet, brown hamburger, onions, garlic, green pepper and mushrooms.
Drain hamburger after browning and add to sauce and continue to simmer.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, oil, honey, lemon juice, parsley, mustard, pepper and onion flakes in small bowl until smooth and creamy.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: great tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Beat eggs, then add to sugar mixture. Then add vanilla and flour.
Put on cookie sheet by teaspoonful. Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven until golden brown.

title: broccoli rice au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yogurt
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Remove from heat after reaching a boil. If you want thicker yogurt, boil milk for 5 minutes.
Let cool to 85° (slightly warmer than lukewarm).
Stir in yogurt - store bought or previously homemade - and stir well.
Pour into large bowl and place in a warm spot where it will not be disturbed. Cover bowl.
Wrap in towels or other available swaddling.
Let stay until set - 5 hours or more.
Place in fridge.
When chilled, use!
I like it best unstirred and drizzled with honey.

title: applesauce cake
directions: This cake can be baked in a loaf pan, Bundt pan or tube pan at 250° for about 90 minutes.
I bake this in paper cups in my muffin or cupcake pans.
Makes 36 to 40.
Bake much less time.
Don't overbake.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add salt and other ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
In lightly greased casserole, alternate tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Top with cheese. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: severe weather throw together
directions: Any ingredients that you desire can be added.

title: corny dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip hot dogs in batter.
Deep fry or use a skillet which can hold approximately 3 inches of oil.
Batter will cover 12 hot dogs.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons oleo in skillet.
Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and lemon pepper.
Add flour, chicken broth and milk.
Add mushroom soup, pimentos and melted oleo.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: mock strawberry candy
directions: Mix milk, coconut, pecans and 2 packages of Jell-O and mix well.
Let stand, unchilled, about 2 hours.

title: turtles
directions: Place 2 pecan halves on a cookie sheet.
Rest the individual caramel on top.
Fill sheet full and heat in a 275° oven for about 12 minutes (just until the caramel begins to soften).
Let cool. Melt chocolate over low heat and dip each piece in chocolate until coated. Place on waxed paper to set.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Separate tuna flakes; mix with soup, milk and seasonings.
Combine noodles and tuna mixture in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pacific casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground meat with green pepper and onion until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, powdered sugar and margarine together.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Blend well together and roll into balls. Lay on cookie sheet.
Put thumb into middle of ball.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind all vegetables together. Mix with 1 cup salt and let stand for 1 hour. Strain out as much juice as possible. Mix remaining ingredients.
Do not cook. Just mix with vegetables; put in jars and seal. Mine made 9 pints.

title: scotch brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.
Melt shortening over low heat in saucepan; remove from heat.
Put brown sugar in pan with shortening; wait 10 minutes and add egg to mixture.
Stir. Add flour, baking powder and salt; stir.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peachy fruit dressing(especially good with peaches and apples)
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients on medium to low speed until smooth, approximately 2 minutes.
Serve over fresh fruit.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: blueberry betty(diabetic dessert)
directions: Melt margarine, then mix in water and bread cubes.
Transfer 1/3 of mixture to the bottom of baking dish.
Top with 1 cup blueberries.
Sprinkle with half the lemon juice and fructose. Repeat the layers ending with the bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with whipped topping.

title: hot vidalia onion spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a quiche dish or Pyrex. Place in a 350° oven until hot. Serve with water wafers.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Put all ingredients into a plastic container. Refrigerate for at least 24 hours. Easy to make and delicious!

title: 12-can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except French fried onions. Put into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Add onions on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: summer delight
directions: Filling:
Mix sugar (1 tablespoon) in cherry pie filling.

title: tapioca cream
directions: Beat egg
whites
until
foamy.
Add
tablespoons
sugar and continue to beat with egg beater until they stand in peaks. Set aside. Mix egg yolk,
tapioca, milk, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil (4 to 5 minutes).
Remove
from
heat.
Pour slowly
into
meringue mixture; blend well.
Add
vanilla.
Let stand
to 20 minutes.
Good served warm.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: lemon ice cubes
directions: Carefully mix water and fresh lemon together.
Carefully pour into ice cube tray.
Freeze.
Combine with Scotch and enjoy.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef with onions and drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Don't overbake! Cool.

title: linguine with parsley pesto sauce
directions: Add spaghetti to boiling water and salt.
Add slowly.
Cover and cook until tender; drain.
Mix other ingredients in blender. Add cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash thoroughly. While squash is draining, combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Mash squash in colander with back of spoon. Transfer drained and mashed squash into bowl with other ingredients. Mix. Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: pork chop and rice dish
directions: In bowl, add rice, soup and 2 cans of water, mushrooms; stir thoroughly.
Add seasonings such as salt, pepper and chopped onions, if desired.
Place pork chops in regular cake pan, pour mixture over top and cover with tin foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Can substitute chicken breasts in place of pork chops.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Cover with ice and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Mix remaining ingredients. Bring to boil; add pickles and onions.
Heat thoroughly.
Do not boil!
pack in hot pint jars and process in hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch mix with dill weed and oil.
Add garlic powder. Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes. Stir after 10 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar; boil and cool. Pour over drained vegetables and let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: my mother's best coffee cake
directions: Combine cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar and set aside.
Cream butter, 1 1/4 cups sugar and eggs until creamy.
Then blend in sour cream, flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla.
Into a greased and floured pan, pour half of the batter and cover with half of the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Pour in remaining batter, then top with remaining cinnamon/sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: orange syrup
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, butter and sugar in a small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves (do not boil).
Remove from heat. Cool slightly.
(Can be made 2 days ahead).
Keep refrigerated.
Rewarm over low heat. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: quick homemade bread
directions: Heat water and butter to 125° to 130°.
Add rest of ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Oil top and let rise 30 to 45 minutes.
Punch down and knead for 4 to 6 minutes.
Divide into 3 portions.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise to double.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese. Sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix Ritz crackers and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion together and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips, grated cheese and sour cream.

title: crisp apple cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well.
Press on bottom of dish.
(Or buy pre-made graham cracker pie crust.)

title: mexican beef and mushroom stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown round stead with onions and garlic in margarine.
Stir in water, salt, chili powder, mushrooms and picante sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, over medium-low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.
Top with sour cream and cheese.

title: kolacky(nut-poppy seed rolls)
directions: Crumble yeast into a small bowl.
Add water and sugar; let stand in warm place until double.
Place flour in large bowl.
Add butter; blend with a pastry cutter.
Make a well; add egg yolks, salt and yeast mixture.
Mix dough until smooth and dough leaves the side of the bowl and hands clean.
Divide dough into 4 pieces. Roll out as thin as possible (rectangular shape).
Spread with filling (nuts and poppy seed, or any filling you wish).
Roll and place on greased baking pan.
Let stand in warm place for 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until brown.
After removing from oven, cover with a damp towel.
Keep covered for about 10 minutes; this makes a nice crust.
Before placing Kolacky in oven, you can brush dough with egg white.
Icing is optional.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt butter and chocolate bar; pour mixture over oatmeal and stir until oatmeal is moist.
Roll mixture into balls and chill. Before serving, roll in sugar.
Yields 18 balls.

title: beef dressing casserole
directions: Mix onion, celery, salt, poultry seasoning and cubed bread. Blend one can mushroom soup with 1 cup milk; mix gently with bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Mix meat, mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add bread mixture; mix well.	Turn into 13 x 9 baking pan.
Spread 1 can undiluted mushroom soup on top.

title: ravioli with broccoli sauce
directions: Heat oil on low in medium sized saucepan.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Saute until garlic is lightly browned (1 to 3 minutes).
Add cream and cook 20 minutes to thicken.
Stir occasionally.
At the same time, cut broccoli into 1 1/2-inch florets.
Cook in water in a separate pot until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Add Parmesan to sauce mixture and stir to blend. Prepare ravioli according to package directions.
Drain.
Add broccoli to sauce and pour over ravioli.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with a rolling pin.
Mix together with other ingredients and roll into small balls.
Roll each ball in Angel Flake coconut.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine potatoes and onion in a large bowl; set aside.
Dissolve bouillon granules in boiling water; stir in vinegar (I use red wine vinegar), oil (I use olive oil), salt and pepper.
Pour over potato mixture and toss gently.
Keep potato slices separated as you are tossing so that each slice will be coated with oil and vinegar mixture.
Sprinkle top with crumbled bacon.
Makes 8 servings.
This is easy and delicious.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken, meat side down, in a shallow baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with onion slices.
Mix, heat and pour the remaining ingredients over the chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, turning chicken after 30 minutes.

title: rice and honey pork chops
directions: In 8 x 8-inch baking dish combine rice, orange juice, raisins and salt.
Stir to mix.
Arrange chops on rice, pressing down into rice.
Drizzle honey over chops.
Cook uncovered with wax paper 16 minutes.
If desired spoon rice over chops during last 2 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings(portuguese)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except wings.
Add wings and marinate
overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trio pasta salad
directions: Cook, rinse in cold water and drain macaroni.
When macaroni has cooled, toss with all other ingredients.
Add salt and pepper. Stir in 3/4 bottle of 16 oz. size Wishbone Italian dressing. Chill well.
Add remaining bottle of dressing and stir before serving.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions into thin rings.
Saute onions in margarine.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until limp and opaque.
Pour half of the onions into casserole dish.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese and crushed crackers.
Pour remaining onions for next layer and repeat the cheese and cracker layer. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until golden brown (about 30 minutes). Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Add pineapple, nuts and zucchini.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coleslaw with italian dressing
directions: Shred the cabbage real fine in bowl.
Mince the garlic and add to all other ingredients in a screw-top jar and shake vigorously. Pour this dressing over the cabbage and toss.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, celery seed and salad dressing mix. Blend well. Refrigerate 24 hours. Serve with raw vegetables. Makes 2 cups.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise. Slip out yolks and mash with fork. Mix in dry mustard, salt, pepper and mayo. Mix well. Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping slightly. Arrange on serving platter and sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.

title: mitcham's peach preserves
directions: Sprinkle sugar over peaches and then pour water over sugar. Cook very slowly to avoid scorching, about 3 to 4 hours.
Keep stirred so they won't scorch.
Remove seed when done.
You may let set overnight and then put in containers.
You can freeze or put in pint jars and hot water bath for 15 minutes.
These are delicious!

title: pumpkin pie(diabetic)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in egg and water mixed together.
Coat chicken in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and spoon off into hot grease.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Place in a bowl in order given.
Do not mix until ingredients have been added.
Then mix well and bake at 350° until done. Makes a 3 layer cake or a 9 x 13-inch loaf cake and 1 dozen cupcakes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and cayenne.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cube bread.
Layer in casserole alternating
bread with crab and shrimp.
Mix all remaining ingredients
together
and pour over bread and meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken and dumpling soup
directions: Boil chicken in 5 to 6 quarts of water for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and add carrots, celery, bouillon and parsley flakes to water.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and cut into chunks and return to mixture.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, sugar, melted margarine and press on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown; cool completely.

title: peanut bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.
Put marshmallows on top of baked cake
and
put
back in oven until marshmallows melt and start to puff up.
Melt together peanut butter chips, butter, corn syrup and
vanilla.
Mix	until smooth.
Add peanuts and Rice Krispies. Put
on
top of marshmallows.
Let stand a few minutes and cut into bars.

title: amanda's cinnamon toast
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a cup.
Toast bread while toast is still hot; butter the toast.
Now sprinkle cinnamon sugar mixture on hot, buttered toast.
Makes 4 warm spicy slices.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Coat a large skillet with the oil.
Heat on medium, add pork chops and brown.
Peel, core and slice apples and toss with cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Turn pork chops.
Add apples. Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: bacon, cheese and olive melt
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut bacon strips into 6 pieces each. Fry until crisp.
In medium bowl, combine cheese, olives, mayonnaise, onion and eggs.
Blend well. Stir in bacon.
Place muffin halves on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spoon cheese over each muffin.
Bake, uncovered, for 12 to 18 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Garnish with paprika or parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: charlie's fried catfish
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Drop into sack containing mixture of corn meal, a little sugar and some salt.
Shake.
Ease fish into deep fryer when oil is real hot; 3 to 4 minutes and it's done.
Dip out with strainer and place on paper towels to dry.
Contains 12 fat grams per person.

title: almond roca bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (light golden brown). Sprinkle chips on hot cookie; let set 1 minute.
Then spread and frost.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Cut in squares while warm and let set up.
Makes many.

title: easy sauteed chicken
directions: Fry chicken using desired coating, do not overcook.
Season with salt, pepper, parsley and garlic powder, drain remaining oil from pan.
Add wine, broth, mushrooms and artichoke hearts. Sprinkle chicken with grated cheese and simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Pound both sides of meat.
Cut meat into serving sizes.
Beat eggs with milk.
Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Dip floured steaks into eggs, then the cracker crumbs.
Brown steak well on both sides.
Reduce heat to medium; cover skillet and cook 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally, until steaks are tender.
Serve with gravy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Mix the next 3 ingredients, pour over salad and mix.
refrigerate about 2 hours or more. Serves 12.

title: meatless shepherd's pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan coated with cooking spray; coat vegetables with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes; set aside.

title: creamy broccoli potato soup
directions: Dice onion, potatoes, carrots and broccoli stems into small pieces.
Cook until almost tender; add tops of broccoli.
Cook until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter; stir in flour, whisking constantly for a couple of minutes.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Drop in cubes of cheese, stirring until melted.
Continue stirring until bubbly and thickened.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ravishing rice
directions: Saute sausage, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Boil 4 cups of water, rice and soup mix for 15 minutes.
Do not drain.
In casserole dish, mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let cook for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6. It's ravishing!

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix and press in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Cover with large melted Hershey bar.
Cool in fridge.
Cut in small squares.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda; add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Beat eggs. Add rest of ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with cream cheese. Soften cheese and beat until smooth.
Spread cheese on slices of cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in mixing bowl, adding eggs, then pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add green pepper and onion; saute.
Add garlic powder and oregano.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and 3 types of macaroni.
Place in baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch dish until cheese is melted.

title: quick sausage bread
directions: Following package instructions, thaw the bread dough and let rise.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown the sausage; drain.
Roll bread dough out on a floured surface until approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Spread sausage evenly over dough to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Lay sliced cheese over sausage; roll dough over sausage and cheese mixture to fit a bread loaf pan.
Place loaf in greased pan and bake for 20 minutes or until the bread is evenly browned on top.
Let cool before slicing.

title: granny's old-fashioned cookies
directions: In
large
mixer
bowl	with
electric	mixer at medium speed, cream
butter
and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add Crisco, vanilla and orange peel. Beat until well mixed.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put zucchini and onions in pan and cover with water.
Ice cubes may be added.
Add salt.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours, then drain.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream
sugars
and butter.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add milk and
mix
well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix. Then
add flavoring and nuts and mix again.
Pour into greased and
floured heavy
Bundt cake pan and bake in preheated 300° oven 1 1/2 hours. Frost with Maple Frosting.

title: heavenly ambrosia
directions: Cut orange first.
When peeling oranges, hold over bowl so all juice will remain in bowl.
Be sure to cut sections deep enough to remove all membrane from orange.
Remove sections by cutting along the side of each, dividing membrane from outside to center.
Peel bananas and slice over oranges.
Dice the apple in very small pieces and add to mixture.
Add cherries, coconut and salt.
Toss lightly and garnish with additional coconut and a few chopped pecans.
This is much better if made several hours ahead of time. Yields 8 servings.

title: spicy tomato meat loaf
directions: Set oven to 425°.
In bowl, combine 1/2 cup mayo, dry mustard and onion.
Add chicken.
Toss to cover chicken.
In separate bowl, mix bread crumbs and sesame seed; roll chicken to coat. Place on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine egg, sugar, flour, cooking oil and flavor in large mixing bowl.
Mash bananas very fine.
Combine with other ingredients.
Mix in nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a loaf pan well.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: old timey-egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cream with butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk and flavoring; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: peachy angel food dessert
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add cake pieces.
Stir gently to coat evenly.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with pie filling.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and onion.
Drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes (or cook in crock-pot on low for 2 hours).
Combine cottage cheese, egg, salt, parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.
In 13 x 9-inch casserole, layer 3 noodles, 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 of cheese mixture and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: southwestern sausage and cheese casserole
directions: Make the day before.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Pour small amount of cooking oil in skillet and sear meat. Add other ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well by hand.
Form into balls.
Bake on ungreased cooking sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: When jello is partially set, fold in cottage cheese, walnuts, cherries and pineapple.
Fold in cream (whipped).
Chill until firm.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Combine with other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together; form into loaf pan.

title: buffalo steaks(modern)
directions: Mix seasonings together and rub into steaks.
Grill on a broiling rack approximately 3 inches from hot coals until done to your liking, 15 minutes for rare and 20 to 25 minutes for medium.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at once.
Do not let stand.
Grease 3 (9 x 3-cm) loaf pans.
Pour within 1/2-inch of top of pan, as they rise.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until pick comes out clean.

title: buttery yeast rolls
directions: Combine the 1 teaspoon sugar, water, and yeast in a small bowl.
Stir to mix.
Set aside until the mixture becomes bubbly. In a large mixing bowl, combine the remaining sugar, milk, egg, melted butter and salt.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup of the flour and the yeast mixture. Mix well.
Gradually add the remaining flour until a moderately firm dough is formed.

Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead the dough until it is no longer sticky. This sometimes takes about 4 to 5 minutes. Place in a large oiled bowl and turn the dough so that all surfaces are oiled.
Cover with a clean towel and let rise in a warm place until doubled. This takes about an hour.

To see if it has risen enough, push your finger into the dough and if it doesn't continue to rise, it is ready. Punch down the dough and pinch off portions about the size of a golf ball. Roll into balls (or shape as desired) and place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover with towel and set in warm place until once again doubled.
This will probably take about 45 minutes. Bake at 400 degrees for about 8 minutes or until rolls start to brown on top.
Brush generously with melted butter and place a piece of aluminum foil loosely over the top of the rolls. Continue baking for another 2 to 4 minutes or until the rolls are fully cooked.
Remove from oven and brush again with butter. Makes about 18 large rolls.

title: four cup salad
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a bowl.
Sprinkle in dry Jell-O while you are stirring.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool and slice to make 4 layers.
Mix whipped topping and pineapple.
Add pudding.
Put icing between layers and on top of cake.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches. Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl. Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Stir in nuts and raisins (optional). Pour into pans. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool slightly. Loosen sides of loaves from pans; remove. Cool completely before slicing. To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than 10 days.

title: flan
directions: Beat eggs on low speed until foamy; add sugar and salt, blending well.
Add evaporated milk, vanilla and cinnamon; blend.

title: christmas salad(3 layer salad)
directions: Mix lime jello with boiling water; dissolve.
Then add 1/2 c. cold water; let get syrupy.
Add maraschino cherries; pour in mold and jell.

title: dessert
directions: Spread the fruit in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the fruit.
Drizzle the melted oleo over the top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chocolate mint snow-top cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: jerk seasoning
directions: Blend until roughly chopped.

title: tomato salad
directions: Cube tomatoes, cucumber and green pepper into bowl.
Mix sugar, water and vinegar until sugar melts; then pour over cubed vegetables.
Let set 45 minutes in fridge and serve.

title: quick pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta by instructions on the package.
Place frozen vegetables in a large colander in the sink.
Pour boiling water and pasta over the frozen vegetables into the colander.
Once the water drains out, move contents to a large bowl.
Add lo-cal dressing to taste.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Saute onion in margarine slightly.
Mix all ingredients and place in Pyrex dish, 12 x 18-inch, sprayed with Pam.
Cook for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: hot broccoli cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish with green onions.
Serve with assorted vegetables or crackers.

title: crockpot broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
(Onion can also be cooked with broccoli, or just added with the other items.)
Drain well.
Put in crockpot with other ingredients.
Cook on low for about 2 or 3 hours.
(Can be baked in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.)

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together peanuts, sugar, white corn syrup and salt. Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes. Stir after cooking 4 minutes. Add margarine and vanilla and cook another 1 to 2 minutes. Peanuts should be light tan. Stir in baking soda until light and foamy. Pour into greased baking sheet and spread to sides. When cool, break into small pieces.

title: country style chicken kiev(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Pound chicken breasts.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, salt, oregano and garlic.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then coat with crumb mixture.
Reserve remaining butter.
Place chicken in ungreased pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Add wine, parsley and green onion to reserved butter.
When chicken is golden brown, pour wine sauce over chicken.
Bake 5 minutes or until sauce is heated.

title: easy rolls
directions: Stir all items together.
Spoon drop into greased muffin tin (makes 12).
Bake at 400° until brown.
Half recipe for 6.

title: chocolate or coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Add eggs with a little of the milk; mix well.
Add the rest of the milk, mixing well.
Cook on top of the stove while stirring constantly.
When thick take off the heat; add vanilla and butter.
Place in pie crust (already baked).
Beat egg whites adding a little sugar until egg whites peak.
Place on top of the pie filling and put back in oven for a few minutes to brown the egg whites.
Let cool.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift or mix dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Add zucchini and nuts. Bake at 325° in loaf pans for one hour.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Cook on high 300° for 5 minutes.
Simmer on low until done.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, nuts, apples and cabbage.
Then add ginger ale and stir well.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat.
Add alternately the milk, vanilla and flour.
Pour batter into baking dish and arrange fruit on top of batter.
Pour fruit juice over this.
Bake at 350° until springs back and golden brown.

title: butterscotch coffee spice cookie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: beef barbecue
directions: In medium mixing bowl, blend together catsup, chili sauce, sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce; set aside. In medium to large pan, lightly brown ground beef with chopped onions. Drain any liquid from beef and stir sauce mixture into beef; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cookies and cream cake
directions: Spread ice cream evenly into two 9-inch round cake pans lined with plastic wrap.
Place in a freezer for at least 1 hour. Remove from pans and return to freezer.

title: everlasting slaw
directions: Mix first four ingredients (the vegetables), in a large bowl or pan that can be placed in refrigerator.
Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar on top of this and set aside.
Do not stir.
Heat the rest of ingredients to boiling.
While still warm, pour over the cabbage mixture.
Let set in refrigerator about 24 hours.
Then stir and enjoy for up to 2 weeks.
Keep in tightly covered container.

title: cranberry tea biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Beat egg until creamy.
Add cranberry sauce and sour cream.
Add to first mixture.
Roll out on floured board and cut into square biscuits. Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Add sour cream.
Mix and add dry ingredients.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put catsup on top and cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: lemon-broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon; set aside.
Squeeze 2 tablespoons juice from remaining lemon; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, beat together oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Stir in flour mixture and fold in apples and almonds.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Unmold cake from pan and cool completely before serving.
Makes 1 cake.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins 20 to 27 minutes at 400°.
Makes 18 medium muffins with less than 2 grams of fat each.

title: quick and easy banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on pie mix, less 1/2 cup
milk.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip in pie mixture.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and then a layer of sliced bananas.
Repeat until all are used.
Pour pie mixture over and let set.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip on top.
I sometimes fold in 1/2 cup coconut in top Cool Whip.

title: german meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls, about 2-inches each.
Heat oil in skillet; brown meatballs.
Drain any fat.
This is good with sauerkraut.
Combine meatballs with kraut. May need to add about 1/3 to 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until meatballs are well done.
Also good with creamed gravy or with tomatoes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
Add other ingredients.
Mix together and chill overnight.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Chop onion and tomatoes.
Add next four ingredients.
Mix together in separate bowl remaining ingredients.
Gently add second bowl ingredients to first.
Garnish with herbs or edible flowers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Brush over ribs, chicken or whatever.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Slit hot dogs to within 1/2-inch of ends.
Insert 2 strips cheese in each slit.
Separate dough into 8 triangles and wrap dough over hot dog, keeping cheese up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up, and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add rice.
Mix soups and broth in separate bowl and pour over rice.	Place chicken breasts on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove lid the last 15 minutes to thicken.

title: haystacks
directions: Cook lentils and add to cooked rice.
Crunch tortilla chips on plate.
Add rice and lentils, shredded cheese, shredded lettuce and top with Ranch dressing.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers in thin slices; while they are drying, mix some flour and salt and pepper.
Roll cucumbers in flour mixture until they are covered.
Fry in lard and flip 'em over.
Serve warm and watch them go.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Remove all seeds from fruit.
Put fruit through food processor.
Pour in bowl.
Add sugar and walnuts.
Let stand or marinate one hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll all ingredients into a large ball and in chopped pecans.

title: aunt rena's raisin pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and vinegar together.
Then add dry ingredients and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: red tomato chow chow
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and hot pepper.
Mix in other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes or until tomatoes are done.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: sunday chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven; cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour, or until tender. Remove chicken; let cool, reserving 2 cups broth.
Bone chicken and chop meat.
Set aside.
Saute celery and onion in butter in a large skillet until tender.
Add reserved broth, cheese, soup, eggs, lemon pepper seasoning and pepper; mix well.
Stir in chicken.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine; press firmly on the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: aunt melba's jello
directions: Cook jello according to package.
Add grated carrots and sliced bananas.
Chill until firm.
Serve topped with whipping cream or spoonful of mayonnaise.
Very good for the holidays.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time until well beaten.
Add all the dry ingredients together.
Put lemon flavor into buttermilk and add to butter and egg mixture. Beat good and put in tube pan, well-greased.
Cook at 325° or 250° or 300° for 1 hour.
Ovens vary in cooking.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Continue beating while gradually adding oil in a thin stream.
Beat until dressing thickens.
Stir in poppy seed.
Refrigerate.

title: ice cream topping(peanut butter fudge)
directions: Put first five ingredients into saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick (about 5 minutes).
Add vanilla and peanut butter.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook chopped onion in fat.
Cook until onions are transparent and drain.
Put tomatoes in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Then reduce to simmer and add spices and garlic.
Then add tomato sauce, tomato paste, ground beef, onions and mushrooms.
Simmer at least 1 hour or more.

title: strawberry pie
directions: After adding hot water to jello, add 8 ice cubes. Stir until dissolved. Add other ingredients. Put into pie shell. Chill.

title: blarney stones
directions: Beat 1 cup egg whites and cream of tartar on high speed of mixer until whites form very stiff peaks,
about 3 minutes; do not underbeat.	Beat the 6 egg yolks 3 minutes.
Add water, extract and sifted dry ingredients (sugar, flour
and salt) in small amounts.
Mix well.
Fold into bowl of
egg whites;
mix carefully.	Pour into a long angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Turn upside down to cool.
Remove
from pan.
Cut into 24 squares.
Ice on all four sides	with
soft icing made of butter, extra egg yolks, cream and powdered sugar.	Roll in chopped ground salted peanuts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the flour and water. Simmer for 2 hours.
Add flour and water mixture slowly to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pork guisantes
directions: Saute pork fat and garlic until brown.
Eliminate any excess oil.
Add lean pork and continue cooking until pork is done.
Mix together salt, bay leaf, pepper, onion, m.s.g. and tomato sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add peas and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add pimento.

title: alta's cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Lay on paper sack to cool.

title: happy new year
directions: Clean thoroughly 12 whole months.
Divide into 365 parts; set aside, preparing one part only at a time as follows:

title: one step microwave lasagna
directions: Cook beef until brown and drain well.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and salt, blending well.
Arrange 1/3 of sauce in 8 x 12-inch microwave baking dish.
Cover with half the uncooked noodles. Spread with 1 cup Ricotta (mixed with chopped parsley, if desired), sprinkle with half the remaining cheeses.
Repeat with second layer and top with remaining 1/3 sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover with double thickness of plastic wrap.
Cook on Medium (50% power) for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle top with additional Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cook on medium about 2 minutes or until cheeses melt.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Stir in flour mixture; shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: licorice snaps
directions: Sift together flour, soda, dry milk, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Cream margarine (or shortening) and sugars.
Add egg.
Blend in dry ingredients and add anise seed and nuts.
Shape into two rolls; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate at least 4 hours; overnight is fine.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: delicious strawberry milkshake
directions: Place frozen strawberries in blender container.
Mix milk, strawberry extract and Sweet 'N Low together; pour over strawberries.
Blend together.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Place pork and beans in a large casserole bowl.
Fry bacon in frying pan preserving grease.
Remove fried bacon, drain and crumble.
Place bacon pieces in beans.
Stir.
Add mustard; stir. Add brown sugar; stir.
Add Worcestershire sauce; stir.
Lightly brown onion in bacon grease; drain and add onion to beans.
Stir. Place, uncovered, in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until crusty top.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook in boiling salt water until tender; drain.
Remove skins. Make a syrup by bringing to a boil water, butter, and sugar. Pour over potatoes. Bake for 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chips and margarine together, cool, add other ingredients. Pour on to and roll in waxed paper.
Refrigerate until set.
Slice.

title: lasagna
directions: Mash sausage and saute first 3 ingredients until brown.
Drain. Add next 7 items to sausage mixture.
Simmer this uncovered 1 hour or until thick.
Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, pepper and parsley in a small bowl.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish and layer as follows:
1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture, 1/2 sausage sauce mixture, 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, then Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Allow to sit 15 minutes before cutting.

title: pizza delight
directions: Cook noodles in water with 1 teaspoon corn oil until soft. In a bowl, mix tomato soup, Parmesan, garlic and oregano.
When noodles are cooked, drain and add to soup mixture.
Layer noodles, cooked sausage, pepperoni and noodles again on top.
Bake in a large bowl in a 350° oven for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mrs. anthony cole slaw
directions: Shred and grate the vegetables.
Mix all together and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for breakfast.

title: green rice(broccoli and rice casserole)
directions: Saute onion and celery while thawing broccoli in small amount of boiling water.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz to onion and celery. Simmer for a minute or so.
Add broccoli that has been well drained.
Add rice and seasonings.
Bake in casserole dish for about 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve while hot.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Fry floured chicken in butter until browned.
Add the rest of the ingredients; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in top of hot double boiler. Add noodles and chopped nuts. Mix well. Keep pot over water, but remove from heat. Drop by tsp. onto wax paper. Let stand until cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add cranberry sauce (dissolved in boiling water) to dissolved raspberry Jell-O.
Add pineapple and juice and mix with Jell-O and cranberry sauce.
Add nuts.
Mix .
Pour half into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan and let set up.
Add sour cream on top.
Pour on the other half cranberry mixture and let set up.

title: san francisco pork loin
directions: Trim pork loin into 1/2-inch slices.
Heat oil in skillet. Brown pork loin slices on both sides.
Remove slices and add a little more oil if needed.
Saute garlic for a minute.
Combine oil, sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar and red pepper.
Place pork loin slices in skillet.
Pour sauce over them.
Cover tightly. Simmer over low heat until pork loin slices are cooked through, 30 to 35 minutes.
Add a little water, 1 to 2 tablespoons, if needed to keep sauce thinned.
Turn once.
Remove to a platter.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Pour sauce over loin slices and fettucine.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except crust.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch thick slices. Cut slices in half. Melt butter in a large skillet; add onion and saute until tender. Put onion in lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.

title: never fail apple slices
directions: Cut lard into flour and graham cracker crumbs until mixture resembles small peas.
Add 1 cup of cold water and mix until dough no longer sticks to sides of bowl.
Peel and core apples; cut into slices.
Add 3/4 cup of sugar or less if apples are sweet (add more if needed).
Then add cinnamon and cornstarch; mix until combined.

title: chicken-roni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine with chicken, cheese, soup, milk, mushrooms, pimiento and mustard. Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain juice from beans.
Chop pepper and onion.
Combine all ingredients and let marinate at least overnight.

title: hot deviled potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions. Heat sour cream, being careful not to boil. Add mustard, salt and sugar; stir to blend.
Stir into hot potatoes; add onion. Stir to blend. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake until heated through. Makes about 5 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into crust. Chill.

title: creamy asparagus chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Saute onions, celery and garlic until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add potato, milk, broth and herbs. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until potato is tender and soup is thickened (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Add asparagus, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Serve with grated cheese.
Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin strips (julienne).
Place layer of potatoes in greased baking dish.
Saute chopped onion until tender (not browned).
Layer onion over potatoes.
Drain spinach and press out most of liquid.
Layer spinach over onions. Layer half of cheese.
Add layer of potatoes.
Add remaining cheese.
Pour cream with thyme and nutmeg mixed in.
Drizzle over casserole and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain most of grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Pour over sandwich buns to serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate candy cookies
directions: Mix all except chocolate together.
Pour mixture (press) into a well-greased cookie sheet and pour over it the melted chocolate morsels.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Remove and slice into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Leave in pan and put back in refrigerator.
Serve cold.
Fantastic!

title: lime pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and lime; cover with water all day or night. Rinse the lime from cucumbers and soak in ice water 3 hours; drain. Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and spices and pour over cucumbers; let stand overnight.
Cook over medium heat and bring to boil; boil 35 minutes and put into jars.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: no cook fast play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add oil and water with food coloring already in it.
Knead with the children and use.

title: fancy jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 4 cups of ice cubes until jello thickens (10 to 15 minutes), then remove ice remaining.
Put aside 1 cup jello.
Mix Cool Whip with remaining jello.
Mix in the 1 cup of plain jello that was put aside.
Pour into serving dish (not mold).

title: haole laulau
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash and drain.
Place half of spinach in a baking pan.
Arrange pork chops on top; brush lightly with liquid smoke.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with remaining spinach.
Slice potatoes 3/4-inch thick; arrange on top of spinach.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: cream cheese sauce for fruit
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in milk.
Chill.
Put on favorite fruit.
Store in refrigerator.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening until onions are yellow.
Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°, removing cover last 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Make your dressing out of the last five ingredients.
An acceptable bottled substitute is any vinaigrette from the Paul Newman's Own or Ken's brands.
Using a vegetable peeler, peel the asparagus spears almost down to the tip.
Be careful to avoid breaking the spears as you work, which is much easier with really fat spears.
Cut off the woody ends, which is usually a couple of inches.
In a large flat skillet, bring about an inch of water to an almost-boil.
Lay spears in water and cook until they just begin to bend when you take them out - just a very few minutes. Carefully remove with tongs to a flat dish and top with the dressing while still hot.
Don't expect them to be swimming in it. Chill overnight and gently turn them over in the marinade a couple of times.
Serve chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar, white sugar and margarine.
Mix in large eggs.
Add flour, soda and cocoa; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate bits.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Mix soup mix, soup and water together.
Cut steak into serving pieces; place in a casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water, salt and dill seed.
Strain.
Place garlic bud in bottom of jar.
Pack sterilized jar in this order; 2 celery sticks, 2 bell pepper strips, and okra.
As you fill jar with okra reverse okra in jar with one stem up and one down; jars are easier to fill.
Reheat vinegar mixture to boiling point and pour over vegetables and seal jars.
A water bath is not necessary.
Keep 6 weeks before opening.

title: chile-noodle bake
directions: Saute
onion
in
margarine
until tender.
Remove from heat and
stir
in
sour cream, cottage cheese, chile, grated cheese (save
cup),
salt and garlic powder.
Stir until well blended.
Lightly toss noodles into mixture until noodles are well coated.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350°
for 30
minutes.
Add
remaining
cheese to top.
Cook, covered,
for moist top, uncovered for crisp top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients for filling and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: french fried onions
directions: In a bowl, beat together flour, milk, egg white and salt. Preheat oil to 365°.
Dip onion ring in batter then in crumbs. Cook in deep hot oil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until brown. Sprinkle with additional salt to taste.

title: buttercup squash
directions: Trim stems off of squash. Cut each squash in quarters. Scrape away seeds. In a large pot bring 2 quarts of water to a boil. Add squash and boil until tender. Remove from water and add mace and pepper to taste.

title: ham and cheese oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Tear ham into small pieces and drop into egg mixture.
Stir in cheese and onion. Pour into greased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.

title: cannibal meat
directions: Combine meat, eggs,
onion, bell pepper and sauces.
In another bowl, use hands
or
fork
to break tomatoes into fine bits.
Add to meat.
Season
with
salt
and
pepper to taste. Add enough crackers to bind mixture into ball.	Chill at least 8 hours.
Serve with	crackers.
You	can
make
into balls or fork on crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed. Drain. Add cream cheese and yogurt blend until smooth. Add garlic salt, pepper and paprika. Mix well and chill.

title: sugared nuts
