directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, bring nuts, sugar and water to a boil.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until syrup mixture has caramelized, and the nuts are well coated, about 12 to 15 minutes.
(The bottom of the skillet should appear dry.)

title: one step cherry cobbler
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Dump the cherry pie filling in.
Do not mix this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until the crust is brown.

title: party chicken
directions: Place chipped beef in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Roll up each piece of breast and wrap with bacon secured with toothpick.
Lay evenly over chipped beef.
Mix undiluted soup with sour cream and pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas.
then drain all juice from pineapple tidbits. Pour pineapple into bowl with bananas.
Peel skin off of oranges. Slice oranges so that chunks are shaped like triangles.
Stir mixture of fruit together and let chill overnight in the refrigerator.
Tastes delicious served with miniature quiches for breakfast!

title: pioneer cake frosting
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream in saucepan and cook on low heat until translucent and thick.
Cool and pour over white or yellow cake.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Melt butter and add to macaroni. Add salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and place in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with paprika and remaining cheese.
Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: my sister linda's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.
Immediately before serving, cook bacon and crumble on top of salad.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
into a stiff dough and then make into small
balls
1/4-inch
thick.
Drop into 4 cups boiling liquid from salt-cured ham or shoulder bone.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Cream in order given, gently blend. Bake in a greased and floured bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour, or until it test done.

title: crusty beef and cheese casserole
directions: Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat oil.
Brown onions and mushrooms.
Add meat.
Combine Ragu, seasonings, sauce and grated Parmesan cheese.
Add drained beef and simmer.
Prepare noodles as per package.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer noodles, 1/2 meat and 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top will brown and get crusty.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: indiana cabbage
directions: Stir-fry 10 minutes over hot burner. Turn off burner and put on lid 10 minutes.

title: make believe champagne
directions: In a punch bowl, or a large pitcher, combine all ingredients. Serve over ice in chilled wine or champagne glasses.
This makes 20 (4 ounce) servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat to a fine cream butter and sugar; gradually add eggs, then mix in lemon and nutmeg.
Mix all well together, then stir in lightly flour, in turn with grated coconut.
Pour mixture in well-buttered pan and bake quickly.

title: carrot-raisin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs, oil, carrots, sugar, orange peel and vanilla on low speed. Scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until moistened, about 15 seconds. Beat on medium speed 45 seconds.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread in pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, milk, flour, soda and spices; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300°
for 15 to 20 minutes or until dry.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat to thicken and blend flavors.
Baste turkey with sauce during the last half hour of roasting.
Make 2 2/3 cups.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place rice in a baking pan.
Arrange pork chops on top of rice.
Pour onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until rice is done.

title: oriental beef and noodles
directions: Combine water, hoisin sauce and vinegar; reserve. Heat a nonstick frying pan over medium heat. Brush frying pan lightly with oil. Add cucumber, red pepper and green onions. Cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir in noodles, 3 teaspoons cilantro and half of the reserved sauce. Place on a warm platter. Pan broil beef eye round steaks for 2 to 3 minutes; do not overcook. Add remaining sauce mixture to frying pan, turning steaks to coat. Place steaks on noodle mixture. Spoon warm sauce over steaks to coat. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. This makes 4 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute onion and beef until beef is browned.
Add corn, salt, herbs and sauce.
Lay one tortilla in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add 1/2 of mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of cheese. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix with other ingredients well and chill until firm.

title: nabisco sugar wafer jell-o pudding
directions: Heat evaporated milk in can in boiling water on stove for 10 minutes.
Take off stove and cool, then put in refrigerator to chill.
This should be done the day before.
The next day, you prepare lemon jello and plain gelatin with 3/4 cup pineapple juice and 3/4 cup of orange juice (no other liquid).
Bring to a quick boil on top of stove.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Let cool.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breast, cut in bite size pieces.
Marinate chicken in Italian dressing and Greek seasoning 1 hour.
Slice onion.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
In large bowl combine chicken, lettuce, onion, chow mein noodles and poppy seed.
Pour salad dressing over salad.
Toss and serve.

title: cream mints
directions: Combine egg white, cream, vanilla, oil of peppermint and desired amount of food coloring; mix well.
Add powdered sugar in one lump sum.
Mix well.
Beat in the butter.
Additional sugar may be needed to make a firm mixture.
Shape into small balls. Place on waxed paper.
Press with fork.
Let stand overnight. Store in container with wax paper between layers.

title: sugar-free finger jello(dietetic)
directions: In a large bowl, combine unflavored gelatin and sugar-free Jell-O.
Add 3 cups of boiling water and stir until Jell-O dissolves.
Pour into a large, shallow pan (13 x 9-inch) and chill until firm.
Cut in squares to serve.
Yield: about 100 (1-inch) squares.
Exchanges: Free.
Calories: None.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix all together and pour over chicken.
Bake in 375° oven approximately 1 hour.

title: potato salad - sour cream
directions: Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill for 2 hours. Add celery and onion.
Chop egg whites; sieve yolks.
Add to whites.
Mix with salad dressing, sour cream and mustard.
Fold into salad.
Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion, garlic, pepper and mushrooms until onion is transparent.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and beans.
Heat through.
Stir yogurt and cottage cheese together.

title: grandma's chicken curry
directions: Slow boil all ingredients, except flour and mashed potatoes, until chicken easily comes off the bone.
Cool and skim fat off the top.
Remove meat from bones.
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef; add cabbage and onion, then rest of ingredients. Bring to boil; cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: coconut mystery cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy throughout.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, blending all well.
Continue beating until mixture will stand in stiff peaks.
Add vinegar and vanilla and beat well.
Fold in coconut.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Place 2 chocolate chips in center of each cookie and cover with small amount of mixture.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for 8 to 24 hours.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter, eggs, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla, water and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: handy pizza sandwiches
directions: Saute meat until it loses its red color; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt. Heat thoroughly. Hollow out centers of rolls and toast lightly.
Divide meat mixture evenly among rolls. Sprinkle each roll with Parmesan and top with Mozzarella. Bake at 400° for about 5 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry in moderately hot pan until browned or done.

title: andy mozetti
directions: Brown meat and onions.
(Drain fat.)
Add spices.
Then add canned spaghetti.
Mix well.
Cook for about 10 to 15 minutes. Add peas just to tender (add frozen).
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chinese rice
directions: Stir-fry all ingredients.
When done add scrambled eggs.

title: baked fish(club member: neil h.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
If fillets are large, cut into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix juice, onion and butter. Dip fish into butter mixture; place in greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Pour remaining butter mixture over fish.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. If desired, sprinkle with paprika.
(I also like to use lemon-pepper.)

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sour cream and butter in medium-size bowl until fluffy. Gradually beat in the confectioners sugar until well blended and smooth.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix 2 eggs, butter and yellow cake mix.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches and lemon juice in bottom of baking dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together until crumbly.
Place by spoonfuls on peaches; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm, plain, with whipped cream or milk.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Spread in bottom of oblong microwave-safe casserole dish.
Cover with soup and stir.
Drain water chestnuts and spread on top of green bean-soup mixture.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes until heated through and bubbly around the edges. Top with French fried onion rings.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes.

title: quick tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Can omit olives.
Chill.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Glaze with lemon juice and powdered sugar mixed to desired consistency.

title: southern banana cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add banana flavorings.	Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts separately.
Combine undrained pineapple, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Chill dough.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and press down slightly.
Bake at 375°.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
In place of water, use 1 cup of orange juice; do not dilute with water.
If recipe calls more than a cup, use water.
Make as many as four layers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Have baked pie shell ready.
In a saucepan, mix cornstarch and salt together.
Add cold water slowly; stir until mixed.
Bring to boiling point.
Stir constantly.
Add about 1/3 quart of berries to cornstarch mixture and cook.
The mixture will take on a beautiful pink color.
Allow to cool.
Add remaining 2/3 quart of cut up berries to cooled strawberry mixture and pour into baked pie shell. Chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: strawberry yogurt salad
directions: Drain fruit.
While fruit is draining, combine in large bowl the yogurt, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and instant vanilla pudding. Add drained fruit and mix well.
Add jello crystals/powder and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serve.
Enjoy!

title: butter cake
directions: Mix or sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream together butter and beaten eggs.
Beat for one minute.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in muffin pans (or use as layer cake) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with green pepper and onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain. Stir in salt, chili powder, pepper and garlic powder. Add tomato sauce and spaghetti and mix well. Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, adding water if needed for a thinner consistency. Spoon into 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and edges begin to brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients except streusel topping.
Beat 30 seconds.
Spread in pan; sprinkle with streusel topping.
Bake 17 to 21 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
While warm, cut into 4 x 2-inch servings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: new orleans red beans and rice(makes 8 servings)
directions: *Or 1 bouillon cube dissolved in 2 cups boiling water.

title: carrot rice loaf
directions: Saute chopped onions in oil and water.
Add and mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in lightly-oiled baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: society sue shrimp
directions: Cook twists and set aside. Saut onions in butter. Add shrimp; saut about 3 minutes until pink. Add cream and Magic. Cook until thickens, stirring constantly (3 to 5 minutes). Toss in pre-cooked twists. Let sit for about 5 minutes. Toss and serve.

title: fish baked in tomato sauce
directions: Put lemon juice on both sides of fish.
Put in baking pan. Heat in skillet; add tomatoes, wine, garlic and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Put parsley, bread crumbs and sauce on fish.
End up with bread crumbs and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste a couple of times.

title: spicy chicken with broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into 2x1/2-inch pieces.
Toss chicken, cornstarch, salt and white pepper in medium bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: cream of pimiento soup(from boone tavern, berea)
directions: In pan, melt butter; stir in flour and seasonings and blend well.
Add milk, stock and pimientos and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serves 10.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add salt, soda and spices.
Sift again.
Combine melted shortening, molasses and water.
Stir in beaten eggs, then flour mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.

title: divine chocolate raspberry sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) round pans. Blend cake mix, water, oil, eggs and 1 cup sour cream in large bowl.
Beat on low speed until moistened (about 30 seconds).
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pans.
Bake and cool cake according to package directions.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown the meat; add the onion and celery and simmer until tender.
Spread meat mixture in a shallow baking dish.
Add in layers the bean sprouts, mushroom soup, cooked noodles and chicken soup.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes for size dish needed.
Add onion and salt and pepper.
Lightly coat with Bisquick (about 1/3 cup for a 1 1/2-quart dish).
Pour half and half to fill about 3/4 way up on container.
Add milk to finish covering potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken-mac saute
directions: Saute macaroni, onion, pepper and garlic in hot Wesson oil until macaroni turns slightly yellow.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add chicken.
Heat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cube chicken and coat with mixture of cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir fry in 2 tablespoons oil until brown, then add water and simmer 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and sweet and sour sauce. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in pineapple. Serve over rice.

title: parsley bread
directions: Split bread in half lengthwise.
Heat butter in saucepan.
Add garlic.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper; remove from heat. Brush 1/2 of bread with mixture.
Cover with second side.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and beaten eggs; mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on warm cake and cover with Chocolate Frosting.

title: crab rolls
directions: Combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper, green onions, cheese, chilies, chili powder and lemon juice together in a bowl.
Fold in crabmeat.
Soften tortillas in microwave for 30 seconds; cover with wet paper towel.
Place filling in one end of tortilla; roll up, jelly roll style.
Place rolled tortillas, seam side down, in the microwave dish and heat for 1 minute.
Cut each tortilla into 3 to 4 pieces.
Serve warm.
Makes 20 to 30 roll-ups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put all ingredients (except cheese) into a large bowl and mix with hands.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Empty bowl into pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil and stir.
Place cheese atop.
Bake until golden brown and liquid is absorbed.
Makes 8 large portions.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and water.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Bake in two 8-inch layers.
Split each layer to make 4 layers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a glass mixing bowl. Cook 7 to 9 minutes on High; mixture should be bubbling and peanuts browned.
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla; cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir quickly, just until mixture is foamy.
Pour immediately onto a greased baking sheet.
Let cool 15 minutes or longer.
Break up peanut brittle and store in an airtight container.
Makes 1 pound and 3 ounces.
Salted roasted Spanish peanuts may also be used.
Put them in a dish towel, gather up corners and rub peanuts in towel to loosen skins.
Pick out nuts (a few bits of skin won't spoil the look).
Add with vanilla and butter.

title: butter crisp cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl cream together Crisco, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg.

title: pear souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl of mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until egg whites stand in stiff, glossy peaks.
With rubber spatula, fold in pears.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake 20 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together taco seasoning, cream cheese and sour cream. Spread on large-size plate which has an edge around it.
Mix together lettuce, green pepper, onion and tomato.
Place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples and sweet potatoes. Cook at a slow boil for 10 minutes.
Cook potatoes; cool and peel. Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel apples and core.
Slice the apples.
Butter a casserole.
Arrange potatoes and apples, overlapping the slices.
Pour sauce over this.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish for layering salad.
Layer as listed.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs and oil.
Cut oranges in small pieces. Add oranges and juice to cake mix.
Mix in oranges by hand.
Pour into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Store in an airtight container. To prepare one serving: add 3 Tbsp. to 6 oz. hot water; stir well. Yield 3 c. dry mix.

title: rhubarb apple mold
directions: Bring rhubarb, water and sugar to boil in small saucepan. Simmer several minutes or until rhubarb is soft.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add rhubarb and cool until syrupy.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spoon into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm. Turn out onto lettuce-lined plate.
Serve with mayonnaise or sour cream.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar. Add vanilla, flour and chopped nuts.
Blend well and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll in balls and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on paper towels to cool.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together egg, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine with rest and mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Shell, devein shrimp and place in boiling salted and seasoned water.
Boil until the shrimp turn pink.
Drain and dice the shrimp.
Dice the green olives.
Combine all ingredients with mayonnaise.
Season with pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers, cocktail breads or spread in celery sticks.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in onions, rice, beef broth, one soup can of water and soy sauce.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cook until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes. Stir in green peppers and pimientos.
Heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 3-quart Dutch oven, saute onion in oil.
Add wheat berries and curry powder and saute 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add rice.
Bring back to boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Cook, covered, for 35 minutes.
Stir in vegetables.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.

Cut in shortening (or melt and cool before adding). Combine orange and egg. Add to dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten. Fold in berries and nuts. Turn into greased loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven 60 minutes. Cool, wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges and juice together.
Pour in two 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Put pudding in bowl.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place between cakes and top and sides. Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet 'n' simple coleslaw
directions: In large 3-quart bowl layer cabbage, green pepper and onion. Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over all.

title: low-fat chinese salad
directions: Toss and add 1 cup fat-free salad dressing and soy sauce to taste.
Toss.

title: meat balls in sour cream
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix together thoroughly.
Mix flour and water.
Cook until thickened. Add sour cream.
Season with additional salt and pepper. Serve with noodles.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: steele's fast appetizer
directions: Cut ham and cheese into squares large enough to cover each roll.
Mix butter, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over rolls.
Top rolls with ham and cheese squares. Pour other half of mixture over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Easy, but great.

title: banana breeze pie
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth and creamy. Put sliced bananas in graham crust.
Pour mixture over bananas. (Can use corn flake crust.)

title: chocolate chip kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add salt and cream of tartar. Continue beating until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Fold in chocolate and add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese broccoli rice
directions: In wok, melt butter or margarine over medium-high heat. Add celery
and
green	pepper.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and
uncooked rice; stir-fry 3 minutes longer.
Stir in
water, soup,
basil
and salt.
Bring to boiling.	Reduce heat;
cover and
simmer
about	20 minutes or until rice and broccoli are done, stirring often.
Makes 6 servings.

title: diabetic jello
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over 1/2 cup of the cool water and allow to stand until gelatine granules are moistened.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in the remaining 1/2 cup cool water.
Add the gelatine and Kool-Aid mixtures to hot water.
Add the liquid sweetener and sugar; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Yields 8 (1/2-cup) servings, 5 calories each.

title: perfect raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water together for 5 minutes.
Cool, then stir in baking soda.
Cream together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add to eggs, nuts and raisin mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture, mixing well.
Refrigerate batter for 1 hour or longer.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool on rack.
Store in tight container.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Add broccoli and boil 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Cover and remove from heat until set.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, then soup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: walnut-mushroom asparagus
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add walnuts and salt to taste.
Spoon over hot cooked asparagus spears that have been well drained.
Yields 8 servings.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Chop tomato and pepper.
Slice onions and mushrooms.
Mince garlic.
Place tomato, pepper, onion, mushrooms and garlic in a large bowl.
Stir in peas and remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.	Stir occasionally.
Drain salad.

title: ham-cheese crumb pie
directions: Mix everything together and fill pie crust.

title: sweet-sour beef stew
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown meat, half at a time, in hot oil. In same saucepan, combine meat, shredded carrots, sliced onions, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with aluminum foil. Grease the foil using part of the margarine.
Place bread crumbs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese in a pie pan.
Mix well to blend.
Pat fish dry with paper towel.
Place milk in an individual salad bowl. Dip fish in milk and then in the bread crumb mixture.
Use remaining margarine to spread evenly on top of all fish fillets. Bake at 500° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 8.
Contains 162 calories per serving, 5 gm cholesterol, 22 gm protein, 5 gm fat and 331 mg. sodium.

title: italian fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut fish into serving size pieces. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over fish. Sprinkle with parsley, basil, oregano and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake until fish flakes easily at thickest part, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownie mix
directions: Sift all of ingredients together.
Cover tightly.
Keep cool. Makes 10 cups of mix.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Heat the ingredients slowly until thickened.
Pour into a large bowl; let cool.
Add fruit (oranges, apples, pineapple, banana, etc.).
Put a little celery salt in fruit of salad.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper, margarine and celery.
Mash Ro-Tel tomatoes and drain.
Add to onion mix and cook about 10 minutes. Mix rice with onions and tomatoes.
Add mushroom soup, parsley and crawfish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Mix together peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat until all chips have melted and mixture is mixed well.

title: squash relish
directions: Shred squash, peppers and onions together and let sit a few minutes.
Bring remaining ingredients to a hard boil.
Add shredded ingredients.
Bring all to a hard boil and put in sterilized jars.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add 1 box of confectioners sugar.

title: never fail drop dumplings
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and cornstarch.
Mix mixtures together and drop in hot broth or beans.
Cook with lid on and don't lift lid.

title: juicy apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, water and cinnamon. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice.
Roll or flatten each biscuit to a 4 1/2-inch circle.
Place small amount diced apples in center of each; fold in half.
Seal by pressing with fork tines or fingers.
Brush with melted butter.
Place in casserole and bake until golden brown.
Delicious served with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: speedy cheese cake
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Put in graham cracker crust.
After 1 hour of refrigeration, put cherries on top.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Top with 3 slices bacon.
Bake in casserole about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and stir to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Heat cherries and 2/3 cup sugar.
Melt butter in Pyrex dish. Mix dry ingredients for batter, then add milk.
Add batter to butter in dish.
Add cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream together in large mixer bowl the sugar and margarine; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add slowly until blended.
Then add nuts, raisins and dates; blend together well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars(like reese's peanut butter cups)
directions: Blend all together.
May have to add some powdered sugar to make if soft but workable.
Put in a large cookie sheet with sides.
Put wax paper on top and press with a rolling pin to make flat.
Melt candy bar and pour over candy.
Smooth with spatula. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Cut in squares.

title: two bean chili(serves 6)
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Coarsely chop green pepper and onion. Saute onion and garlic in large saucepan in oil until tender, about 4 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, beer, chili powder, cumin, hot sauce and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in beans and green pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, another 15 minutes.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine until smooth.
Mix with flour and Rice Krispies.
Dough will be stiff.
Make small balls and mash into 1/4-inch flat circles.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 to 75, depending on size. May be frozen.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and liquid in a large mixing bowl; the batter may be lumpy.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Melt butter and pour 1/3 of butter over the batter and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour 1/3 of butter over bread and bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour last 1/3 of butter over bread and bake 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool for 30 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and strain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Bake at 320° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy and quick pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Mix 2 ingredients together. Spoon into muffin cups and bake! These have a very thick texture.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in 1/2 cup cooking oil 15 seconds.
Put 2 tablespoons cheese, 1 tablespoon onion and chopped chicken in each; roll up.
Put seam side down in 11 x 7-inch pan (11 x 13-inch pan if double recipe).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of butter and add the flour to make a cream sauce.
Add soup.
Add mushrooms which have been sauteed in 2 tablespoons of melted butter.
Return pan to heat.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes, until smooth and thick. Combine egg yolk and cream in small bowl.
Slowly stir into egg mixture 2 tablespoons of hot sauce.
Add to mushroom and sauce mixture.

title: pineapple nut sandwich spread
directions: Soften cake of cream cheese with either milk or mayonnaise to good spreading consistency.
Cook pineapple and sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese mixture and pineapple mixture.
Just before spreading sandwiches, add nuts.

title: seafood scampi(serves 4)
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet
on medium-high.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic 3 minutes.
Add remaining Scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettuccini; toss and heat through.

title: casey's chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until it falls apart easily (1 to 2 hours). Shred chicken and set aside. Chop onions and saute until clear, but firm. Combine soup, sour cream, Pace and Cheddar. Add onion and mix. Set aside 2 cups of pre-chicken mixture. Pour mixture into chicken to get a thick paste. Spoon chicken paste into fajita shells and roll into tube shape. Place side by side in lasagne pan. Cover with leftover soup mixture and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar and chopped tomatoes. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; reserve juice.
Make Jell-O, following directions on box, except use fruit cocktail juice.
Add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate until almost jelled.
Then push cake down in Jell-O.
Return to refrigerator until firm.
To loosen cake from bowl, sit in cold water about a
minute; run a knife around edge.
Put a plate over bowl and turn over.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1/2 of berries.
Drain juice into measuring cup.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Pour liquid into saucepan.
Stir in sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook over low heat until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add few drops of food coloring if desired.
Let stand until cool.
Gently fold in rest of berries (quartered).
Pour into cool shell.
Chill for at least 2 hours. Serve, top with whipped cream.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all together and blend in blender or with an electric mixer for 5 minutes.

title: greek style penne
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Set tomato mixture aside. Cook pasta in large pot in salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain. Add hot pasta to tomato mixture and toss to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.

title: sweet potato banana casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, sugar, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
If dry, add a bit of milk.
Put half of the mixture into a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with mashed bananas. Add remaining potato mixture, then add topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to directions.
Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove when hot, but do not boil. Toss in noodles.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Place bacon and shrimp onto round toothpicks shish-ka-bob style (2 shrimp and 1/4 slice of bacon on each toothpick).
Place about 1/2 of the shrimp on microwavable plate covered with paper towel.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.
Turn plate 1/2 turn and microwave 3 minutes on High.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine 4 cups water and bouillon cubes to make broth.
Add celery, onion and potatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Add the two soups and 2 cans of water.
Heat through and add cubed Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Freezes well.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs and salad oil.
Rinse seeds out of chilies; finely chop them and add to egg mixture.
Add corn, sour cream, corn meal, salt, baking powder and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Mix and pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients, then stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and completely cool.

title: * bakeless cake *
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add pineapple, nuts and cream.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Cover bottom of loaf pan with crackers and spread this mixture over graham crackers.
Dissolve jello in water as per directions on box and add 1 tablespoon sugar.
When nearly set, pour over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut in squares the size of the graham crackers.
Top each serving with whipped cream.
Serves 12 to 15 or figure 1/2 of the amount of graham crackers used.
Very rich.

title: goodies
directions: In boiler, melt almond bark.
Mix with cereal and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.
(Mixture will be thin. It takes a while to harden.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked oysters or salmon
directions: Mix all together.
Grease.
Pour in a baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Bake uncovered.

title: harvest cheesecake
directions: Mix all together.
Press into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Sprinkle over 1 package yellow cake mix, no lumps. Drizzle over 1 1/2 sticks of melted butter.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: beef cheese log
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add olives, parsley and onion.
Shape into a log on waxed paper.
Chill.
Roll in dried beef.

title: stone ground wheat bread
directions: Mix lukewarm water, 1 tablespoon honey or molasses, 2 tablespoons yeast and wheat flour.
Cover and let set for 20 minutes or as long as all day.
Mix in remaining ingredients, adding white flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Stir until dough begins to pull away from the sides of the bowl.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes. Divide into two loaves; place in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pans.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If you make 1 loaf and a dozen rolls, bake rolls at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato tomato pizza
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown the hamburger.
Add soups and milk.
Add potatoes and oregano to mixture; mix well.
Cover with pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Let cheese and butter soften at room temperature, then blend. Stir in flour.
Chill slightly (about 1 hour).
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls, then place in ungreased mini muffin tins.
Press dough against bottom and sides of cups.

title: pistachio congealed salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: holiday fudge(yield: 2 dozen pieces)
directions: 1. Spray a square cake pan with non-stick spray.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, salt and celery seed; cool.
When cool, pour over pickles, onions and pepper.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Wash red snapper.
Place in a baking pan.
Pour water into pan.
Season snapper well with lemon pepper, adding only a dash or two of the other seasonings.
Place onion, celery and garlic clove broken into pieces inside of snapper.
Bake at 325° until cooked.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ham, cheese, broccoli and soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir remaining ingredients until dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls evenly over broccoli mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, Ricotta and eggs mixed with vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Make balls in palm of hand (keep hands slightly wet with water).
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown on bottom.
Cool and frost.

title: broccoli casserole no. 1(serves 6)
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on packages.
Cook rice.
Layer in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place in a boiler and barely cover with water.
Cook until the potatoes are slightly tender. Drain most of the water off.
Add sugar and margarine to the potatoes in the boiler.
Continue cooking until the liquid thickens.
If potatoes become to soft, remove them from the boiler and continue cooking the liquid until it is the right consistency and return the potatoes to the boiler.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Mix together the wine vinegar, soy sauce and sugar; set aside. Coat chicken with cornstarch.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok. Add chicken; stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes until cooked.
Remove from pan.
Add onion, garlic, red pepper and ginger; stir-fry 15 seconds.
Add wine vinegar mixture and chicken, stirring to coat chicken.
Mix in peanuts.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine orange juice and lemon juice and add water to make 2 cups and heat.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Add cranberry sauce to hot jello, stirring until dissolved.
When mixture is cool, add pineapple, celery and grapes (and pecans, if desired).

title: simple chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 1/2 hour.

title: orange sugared pecans
directions: Boil sugar and orange juice together until soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; add grated orange rind and pecan halves.
Beat until creamy.
Pour out and separate into pecan halves.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Place in a large kettle.
Cover with water.
Soak one hour.
Drain.
Cover beans with water again. Add ham hock and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Prepare the cake according to directions, making two (8-inch) layers. Split both horizontally after they have cooled. Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut and chill. Spread all but one cup of the sour cream mixture between the four layers. Blend the remaining cup of the mixture with the whip cream and spread on the top and sides of the cake. Seal in an airtight container and refrigerate for three days before serving. Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Sift flour with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.

title: herb bread
directions: Melt margarine; mix in herbs.
Pull biscuits apart; dip individually into mixture.
Place in a Bundt pan on sides, not flat.
Pour remaining mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert onto plate immediately.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and store in tight container

title: vegetable salad and dressing
directions: Mix and serve.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.
Tastes best if you mix and let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, milk, baking powder, coconut, nuts and pineapple.
Crush graham crackers and mix.
Grease pan and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check with a straw or toothpick.
Let cool and pour pineapple juice over cake and make icing.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil Karo syrup, brown sugar and margarine in a saucepan for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and stir.
Add the baking soda and stir until the mixture stops rising.
Pour over the popcorn and mix.
Put the caramel corn in two 9 x 11-inch cake pans and cook in a 225° oven for 1 hour.
Stir the caramel corn every 15 minutes.
Break apart the caramel corn while it is still warm.

title: homemade perfume
directions: Crush foods with a hammer on pieces of waxed paper.
Place crushed foods into container.
Add water to cover overnight.
Pour off clear juice into different containers.
Use within a few days.

title: no bake brownies
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until melted.
Cook and stir to a full all over boil, 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from heat, gradually stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into a 9-inch buttered pan, chill 1 hour.

title: jellied fruit salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in water; add strawberries, pineapple, bananas, sour cream and marshmallows.
Chill until set.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and bake at 350° until done.

title: perfect seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve on crisp lettuce leaves or use as sandwich filler.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well before using.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: ruth's  no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo together well. Bring to a boil in saucepan and remove from heat. Add oats and mix, then peanut butter and mix. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° (15 minutes).
Cake wil be dark and hard; add one can of crushed pineapple (juice and all); pour over top of cake, then spread one can white cake frosting over that.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes. Less time if potatoes are

quartered. Drain well and mash. Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until smooth. Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika. Spoon mixture into lightly buttered 2 qt. casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from fridge 15 minutes before baking. Bake uncovered at 350° until thoroughly heated. Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover meat with 6 cups water; heat slowly and simmer 3 hours, or until tender.
About 30 minutes before serving, add the vegetables and salt.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan.
Add just enough water to cover. Boil 10 to 12 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain.
Mix ginger with sugar; sprinkle over carrots.
Add melted margarine and stir gently.
Sprinkle with parsley just before serving.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix; warm sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the crumbs, 1 stick butter
and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix well. Spread in dish.

Put in a 350° oven to set crust for a few minutes. Mix for 15 minutes 2 sticks soft butter, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Spread on top of crust. Spread pineapple on top. Spread sliced bananas. Spread cherries, then Cool Whip.
Put nuts in or on top, if desired.

title: honey baked chicken(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken pieces in shallow baking pan.
In small saucepan, melt butter with a whisk.
Mix in honey Dijon mustard, salt and curry until well mixed.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add the flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add the lemon flavoring.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Pound
out
chicken
breasts
from
center
to 1/8-inch thickness between 2 pieces clear plastic wrap.
Divide broccoli, cheese and butter evenly into 4 parts.
Place in center of flattened
chicken breasts.
Roll chicken up to cover broccoli mix.
Coat	with flour; dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs. Place in lightly greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: german cabbage
directions: Bring to a boil the cabbage (cut up) and 2 cups water, then simmer until cabbage is done.
If cooked in a good pan that does not require water, use half of water.
Add the bell pepper (cut up), 1/4 cup tomato sauce, 1 fresh tomato (cut up) and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add bacon (crisp).

title: chili verde
directions: Cut fat from steaks.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Fry pork until done.
Remove meat.
Fry onions until tender.
Make gravy with drippings, flour and water.
Return meat and onions to gravy with all other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with refried beans and Spanish rice.
Yeah hawwwww!!!

title: breaded steak
directions: Cut steak into small serving pieces. Dip in eggs, a piece at a time.
Put in cracker crumbs and press into meat with fingers. Fry until golden brown.
I serve with lemon wedges.

title: old-fashion apple pie
directions: Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large mixer bowl about 30 seconds. Blend in ice cream. Fold in whipped topping until smooth. Freeze if necessary until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add soups, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies.
Heat to boiling.
Place Doritos in a long casserole dish.
Pour skillet mix over Doritos.
Slice cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Melt butter with onions.
Mix all ingredients together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix in order given, except mix soda with applesauce.
Fold in nuts and raisins after batter is well mixed.
Bake in angel food pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250° to 300°.
Cake is done when a straw comes out clean.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Cook cake as the box
says
in	13 x 2-inch pan. Simmer pineapple and sugar.
Punch
holes	in cake and pour pineapple over this.	Cool.
Mix
pudding
as
directed
and spread over this; add 1/2 of
coconut
to
pudding
before you spread over pineapple.	Spread Cool Whip
over	this
and add chopped nuts and remainder of coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until browned, drain off fat.
Stir in mushrooms (with liquid) and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until all liquid is gone.
Great side dish!

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well flour, soda, salt, sugar and cocoa.
Add Crisco, egg and milk-cream.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with marshmallow. Return to oven to bake 2 minutes more.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a large soup pan, simmer onions, celery and hamburg. Separate the hamburg as you're frying it.
Add water and beef cubes.
Mash the tomatoes; add them as well and cook for 10 minutes.
Add the macaroni and stir often.
Add Veg-All and mushrooms.
Sprinkle oregano and parsley flakes.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Store lightly covered for a month in refrigerator before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine the water, sugar and cornstarch and cook until thick and clear.
Add food coloring and 4 tablespoons of dry gelatin. Cool.

title: cool rise cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together sugar or honey, salt and yeast.
Melt together margarine, water and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour until it starts to fall apart (soft dough, not sticky).
Let rest 20 minutes. Cover with waxed paper and towel; let rise.
Punch down, roll out and spread with butter, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll up and cut to make individual rolls.
Put in 2 square 8 inch pans or 3 cake pans. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pans) until light brown.

title: festive sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 T. juice.
Cook chicken in hot oil until no longer pink inside.
Add peppers, onions, and pineapple chunks to pan.
Stir in sweet and sour sauce, and reserved juice and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve over rice.

title: italian casserole with biscuit topping
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water, garlic and spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add vegetables and 3/4 cup cheese.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange biscuits (that have been pulled apart to make two) in an oval over the top.
Sprinkle with a little oregano and put the remaining 3/4 cup cheese in the center.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add pizza sauce, drained mushrooms and oregano.
Cook a little.
Cook rotini; drain off water.
Add 1/2 cup milk and let it set for a few minutes.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Mix flavored gelatin separately using 1 1/4 cups hot water for each package. Soften 2 packages unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup water. Set aside. Beat together cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk. Heat the remaining 2 cups milk to almost boiling, then add 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in the softened unflavored gelatin. Add cream cheese mixture and vanilla.
Stir until smooth. Cool.

title: my best pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour and salt, almond and vanilla extracts and stir well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan (use large tube pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have the butcher grind the ham and the pork.
Mix all ingredients and bake 2 hours in oven at 325°.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the soup and sour cream. Shape into balls. Brown over low heat for about 10 minutes. Drain. Add the soup. Simmer about 10 minutes. Add the sour cream and serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, crumbs, onions, eggs, and seasonings. Form into balls. Brown in electric skillet. Remove meatballs and drain off all grease. Mix ketchup and jelly. Heat on low until jelly melts. Return meatballs to sauce and simmer until done.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, buttermilk dressing, mayo or salad dressing, sugar and garlic powder.
Toss with peas, cauliflower flowerets, broccoli flowerets, bacon and onions.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with sugar. Add oil and mix well. Fold in flour mixture with zucchini. Do not overmix. Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until done.
(If crust edges start to get too brown, cover with foil.)

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil.
Remove from heat when it boils.
Add (pre-measured) flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Beat in eggs and sour cream.
Bake in a 17 x 13 x 1-inch pan (cookie sheet/jelly roll pan), greased and floured, for 22 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix meat loaf and pat out flat on aluminum foil, 10 x 12-inch. Lay strips of ham and cheese down middle.
Fold foil over each end and press meat to seal.
Lift meat from foil to baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise. Add crumbled bacon. Just before serving, add tomato.

title: fudge chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line baking sheet with aluminum foil shiny side up.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream sugars and butter or margarine.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla until well combined.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool on wire rack completely before peeling foil from cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Set aside.
Mix 3 teaspoons cornstarch with water and set aside.

title: bath salts
directions: Put Epsom salt in a glass or metal bowl, not plastic because it may stain.
Mix in the glycerin, a few drops of food coloring and enough perfume to make a fragrant mixture.
Slowly add this mixture to the Epsom salt and stir well.
For a decorative look, place the bath salts in a pretty jar and add a bow.
Now you can enjoy luxurious baths without spending a fortune.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into floured pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add milk and sugar a little at a time.
Beat the mixture until creamy and smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in a 9-inch graham cracker crust and freeze.
Keep frozen until about 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes in mixing bowl; add all other ingredients except pineapple.
After mixing all ingredients, place in medium to large casserole dish.
Place in preheated oven at 350°.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir.
Top with marshmallows.
Put back in oven until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, sour cream, bacon bits, onion, sugar and spices.
Pour over peas.
Let stand as is, or gently stir together.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Dip clusters in egg white, then into granulated sugar.
Allow to dry on cake rack for 1/2 hour.
Repeat frosting process.
Allow to dry thoroughly.
May be done day before.
Store in refrigerator.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add Kool-Aid and sugar; stir.
Add 6 cups water, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze in plastic jug.
Thaw 3 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Add pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese.
Fold in cottage cheese and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Mix all dry ingredients well, add oil and stir well. Pour into paper sack or a large bowl lined with paper towel to absorb oil.
Shake sack periodically (you may have to change sacks).

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Heat the chili in a microwave-safe dish until quite warm (about 3 minutes). Cut the cream cheese into cubes and stir into chili.
Heat again until hot and stir well until the cheese is no longer chunky, but smooth. Serve with tortilla chips; lightly salted ones are better with this as it is fairly salty.
(Staggs House chili makes the best flavor.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Use a large bowl and mix pudding and pineapple until pudding is dissolved.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: tom's specialty(fish)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine all ingredients except fish.
Next, add fish.
Place in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: *Apples, bananas, pineapple, grapes, etc., may be used.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours. Pack in sterilized jars and cook in canner (not pressure cooker) for 1 hour.
This should make 12 quart jars, depending on size of the tomatoes.

title: broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and celery in the butter.
Add cooked broccoli, mushroom soup, garlic cheese, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco to taste.

title: broccoli on the ritz
directions: Cook broccoli with salt and drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler with 1/2 cube of oleo.
Toss with broccoli.
Crush crackers and mix other 1/2 cube of oleo.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put one layer of cracker mix, then broccoli and end with the cracker mixture on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 30 minutes or until the top is golden brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan; stir in crushed pretzels and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cheese and sugar and add whipped topping; blend.
Spread over cooled crust.
Let set 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add frozen strawberries and allow to begin to congeal.
Pour on top of cheese mixture.
Refrigerate to finish congealing.
Cut in squares for servings.

title: cheese garlic bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together well.
Split bread lengthwise.
Spread cheese and garlic mixture on both sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; cream with Miracle Whip.
Add alternately with flour and boiling water.
Add 2 egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and add last, folding into batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in well-greased pans.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and pineapple in large bowl.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan (I sometimes use sheet cake pan).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° (sheet pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes).
Cake will be golden brown.
Test with toothpick.

title: brewer's chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low-fat fruit cake bars
directions: Sift flour with sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Put in large bowl.
Put soda into boiling water.
Mix.
Add to flour.
Add mayonnaise, mix well.
Add cocoa, brandy, raisins and candied fruit.
Mix well.
Spray 13 x 8 1/2-inch pan with Pam.
Add mixture.
Decorate top of cake with candied cherries, cut in half. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Each square contains 30 calories and 1 gr. fat.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: In a crock-pot, put currant jelly,
mustard and grape jelly. Let dissolve until liquid.
Add wieners. Cook until wieners are done.
You may use an electric skillet, letting wieners cook, then setting on low to keep warm.

title: cedar key hoe cake bread
directions: Mix
well
and	fry in iron skillet until brown on both sides. Makes about 2 cakes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Spread pineapple in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add pie filling, spreading gently.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on pie filling, top with pecans. Combine butter and reserved pineapple juice, drizzle on mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Top with whipped topping.

title: annie's baked corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla and milk.
Pour over rest of ingredients.
Bake at moderate heat (350°) for about an hour or until done.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir in.
Blend in walnuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°. Drop rounded tablespoonful 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes until delicately browned.
Top with Burnt Butter Glaze.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix peanut butter, sugar and Karo syrup until melted.
Mix with Special K.
Pat mixture into an 8 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Put into 300° oven until chips are melted.
Spread with knife.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all the ingredients in bowl.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut when cooled.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; let cool. Add yeast, dissolved in water, beaten egg and remaining ingredients, then knead. Let rise. Roll out and cut. Let rise about 1/2 hour. Fry in deep fat.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pick off bone.
Keep chicken and broth.
In a large bowl, mix together flour, water and egg.
Add as much flour as needed so dough will not be sticky.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Drop into boiling water and chicken.
Do not stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Cook onion in butter over low heat until tender; do not brown. Combine meats, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Mix in flour and beat in egg gradually.
Beat in cream and add onion; mixture should be light and fluffy.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Lightly brown in skillet, shaking skillet to turn.
Remove fat.
Add consomme; cook, uncovered, for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup (undiluted) and heat until hot.
Meatballs can be served over cooked rice or noodles.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt butter
in
a 12-inch skillet that can be put into oven. Lightly
mix
flour,
milk,
eggs
and nutmeg together. Pour batter into
skillet
and
bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle
with powdered sugar and return to oven briefly. Sprinkle with lemon juice and serve.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Set aside. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with cocoa and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: quick sweet and sour chicken(microwave)
directions: Drain pineapple juice into 2-quart casserole.
Blend juice and cornstarch; stir in corn syrup, ketchup, soy sauce, vinegar and garlic.
Stir in chicken.

title: appetizer spread
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, combine water and sugar to a boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Add cranberries and let cook until cranberries pop and sauce is thickened, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Cut apricots into small pieces and add to mixture. Stir in lemon juice. Let cool and fold in almonds. Spoon over cream cheese; serve with favorite crackers.

title: chili shepherd's pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook hamburg and onion with chili powder until onion is tender and meat cooked through. Stir in half the soup, water and salt and pepper.
Bring all to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a medium size saucepan.
Add water and Jell-O.
Cook on low heat until thick and clear.
Stir constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Slice strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip when cold.

title: most requested chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Line bottom of pans with wax paper.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl frequently.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans. Immediately remove wax paper.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Put a large boneless chuck roast in the crock-pot and cover with ketchup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, Accent, brown sugar and mustard.
Cook on low overnight.
Shred beef and return to liquid until ready to serve.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Cook ground beef with onion and green pepper until done. Drain grease out.
Put meat on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Add green beans as second layer, then put a whole bag of Tater Tots on top layer.
Pour a mixture of a can of cream of mushroom soup with a can of milk over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for an hour.

title: eddie's no fuss chicken and vegetable pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 450° or prepare grill.
Prepare 4 (12 x 12-inch) heavy-duty aluminum foil sheets.
Cut a deep pocket in each chicken breast half.
Toss the vegetables with 1/2 of the dressing and divide evenly, filling each pocket.
Brush the rest of the dressing over both sides of the chicken breast.
Fold the foil around each stuffed pocket and grill for 20 to 25 minutes or make on a cookie sheet for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: baked fish(serves one)
directions: Place fish on large piece of aluminum foil.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Alternate potatoes, mushrooms, onion, celery and cauliflower or broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap edges of aluminum foil up over top of fish and fold over itself.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: fresh strawberry or peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt with 2 tablespoon water in a paste.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over; cook slowly, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and food coloring.
Cool; add fruit (sliced) and put into baked shell. Chill.
An hour or so before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; add precooked meatballs and heat or cook in crock-pot.

title: baked crab casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Dice 4 slices of bread and the trimmed crusts and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix crab, mayonnaise, onion and celery and spread over diced bread.
Place the 4 whole slices of bread over crab mixture.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: nine-day cole slaw
directions: Stir together cabbage, onion, green pepper and 1 cup sugar. Bring to a boil the salad oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and remaining sugar.
Immediately pour this hot mixture over the cabbage mixture.
Chill overnight before serving.
Keep stored in the refrigerator.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Make Jell-O according to package directions using 1/2 amount of water called for.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together in bowl the soup, milk and sour cream.
Layer the potatoes, onions and cheese in a baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand a few hours, overnight if possible.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream butter and cream cheese, then add sugar, one cup at a time.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add flavorings.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour 50 minutes to 2 hours.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream together remaining 1/2 cup sugar and butter, mixing well.
Add flour and egg, mixing well. Stir in vanilla.
Spoon mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: This quick new way cuts oven time.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake mix in pizza pan for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix pudding and milk.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip, then add pudding and mix together.
Spread on top of cooled cake. Drain pineapple and spread on top of cheese mixture, then top with nuts and coconut.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Whisk together the first 6 ingredients.
Add salad dressing, whisking until completely smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours for flavors to blend.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.
Also, good as a dip for veggies.

title: citrus brunch fruit
directions: Combine orange and grapefruit sections.
Make syrup from sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add 1/2 cup lemon juice and cool.
Pour syrup over oranges and grapefruit and marinate overnight.
Just before serving, add sliced avocado.
This can be drained and served on lettuce or you can serve undrained in cups, etc.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: black bean tacos
directions: Use a nonstick pan or wok.
Using a garlic press, squeeze garlic cloves into pan and add oil.
Add the five vegetables listed, stirring constantly.
Cook until crisp, 6 to 8 minutes on high heat.
Next, chop tomatoes and add along with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Stir well.
Add the sherry and stir again. Cover pan and continue cooking 2 to 4 minutes.
Excellent.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: On cookie sheet, unroll crescent rolls.
Flatten and bake as directed; cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Snack serves 20 to 25.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Use wooden spoon, not mixer.
Mix eggs and sugar very well. Add melted shortening.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to batter; mix well.
Drop by round tablespoonful onto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Remove when brown around edges.

title: corn puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together, combining well.
Bake in greased casserole dish in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix well by pouring ingredients through a sifter.

title: apricot ribbon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix well.
Press onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. Spread crust with preserves; cover with meringue.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Continue baking 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cut while warm.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, paprika and pepper.
Brown rice and onion in butter (optional).
Spread rice mixture in roaster or buttered baking dish.
Add broth and celery salt.
Place chicken on top of other mixture.
Cover dish tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes, or until meat is tender.

title: easy italian chicken and vegetables
directions: Place drained green beans on one side of baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced potatoes on the other side and chicken breasts in center.
Sprinkle Good Seasons mix over everything. Melt butter; pour over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creme de menthe frappe
directions: Put creme de menthe and ice into blender container.
Cover and blend at high speed until smooth.
Pour into 2 cocktail glasses. Makes 2 servings.

title: sour cream cocoa cookies
directions: Mix together.
Chill dough about 1/2 hour.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.
(Do not freeze.)

title: chewies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in other ingredients. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Grease baking dish or casserole dish.
Place a single layer of bread slices on bottom of dish (crusts may be removed, if desired).
Add a layer of meat slices (any meat may be used, preferably not too much fat).
Add a layer of Cheddar cheese, grated or sliced.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Adjust the quantity of eggs and milk so they are sufficient to fill dish to approximately 3/4 level.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: steve's grilled chicken
directions: Combine
first	4
ingredients in a large shallow dish. Add chicken breasts and turn several times. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: microwave strawberry jam
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in an 8-cup batter bowl. Microwave on Full power 4 to 8 minutes to dissolve sugar (stir every 2 to 3 minutes).
Then microwave on 50% power 5 to 8 minutes, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into containers and refrigerate or freeze.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, adding 1 teaspoon vanilla. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan, according to directions.

title: kentucky sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer for 10 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: *Pecans may be used instead of walnuts.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat mushroom soup and cream cheese until hot; add gelatine mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Cool.
Add 1 cup mayo, celery and onions.
Rinse crab; crumble fine.
Mix well; pour into mold; chill.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: creamed sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in small amount of salted water in covered pan; drain well.
In medium saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender; add flour, brown sugar, mustard and salt and stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add sour cream and mix; add sprouts, stirring gently.

title: aunte pe jays chicken casserole
directions: Mix the soups, rice, milk and mushrooms and pour into 9X13 inch baking dish. Top with chicken. Drizzle melted butter over the chicken and season to taste. Cover and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken with herbs soup

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Pour lime jello into shallow pan. Place in refrigerator.
When lime begins to set, add crushed pineapple and return to fridge.
Set thoroughly.
After lemon jello is set, whip and add cream cheese.
Blend thoroughly. Spread over lime mixture.
Keep chilled until time to serve.

title: ham junk
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients and bring to simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add meat to sauce.
Try to separate meat into individual slices as much as possible.
Stir meat into sauce so sauce mixes well, covering all.
Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
You can serve immediately on buns, but it is better to make a day ahead and reheat.
Yield:
6 to 10 sandwiches.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Chop onions, mince garlic, dice celery and zucchini and green pepper.
Cut up tomatoes.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add all items together.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes until vegetables are done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
