Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks; stir in mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients.
Spoon into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: beef and baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add all ingredients except cheese and rolls.
Pour meat mixture into ovenproof dish; top with rolls and bake until rolls are brown. Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts, about 25 minutes in all.

title: caesar salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, add wine vinegar, olive oil and black pepper to mashed cloves of garlic and anchovy paste (according to taste).
Add egg yolks, mustard and lime juice.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: fena's onion sandwiches
directions: Chop onion fine; combine with water, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cool overnight.
The next day, drain onions.
Use white bread.
Trim brown edges off.
Spread mayonnaise on both sides of bread.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and then spread onions, not too thick.
Put together and cut into finger sandwiches.
Can be frozen and thawed to be used later.

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and white sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased pan.
Over batter, sprinkle 1/2 cup light brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo and flour.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Blend oleo and flour; add to corn. Cook until desired thickness is reached.
Yummy!

title: presbyterian chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt and celery stalks; cook until chicken is tender.
Season bread with sage, thyme and pepper.
Layer chicken, cut into small pieces, with the seasoned bread cubes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Dot with butter; pour broth from chicken (strained and celery removed) over the casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly with rotary mixer.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture, just until blended.
Divide batter equally between 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until wood pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire racks to cool thoroughly.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order except cheese.
Pour half of batter into greased iron skillet; add half of cheese.
Add remaining batter and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw 2 loaves frozen bread (not raised).
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pull one loaf of bread apart in small pieces and put in pan. Mix brown sugar, milk, butter, pudding, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour mixture over th 1st loaf of bread.
Pull the 2nd loaf apart and put on top of bread and mixture in pan.
Cover with wax paper and let rise until pan is full.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn pan over on large tray and let cool.

title: bob's favorite onion pie
directions: Put one pie crust on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
On top of pie crust, add cheese (cut into cubes) and onion.
Pour milk over cheese and onion.
Sprinkle pepper over all.
Put second pie crust on top and pinch edges to seal.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes and cut, unpeeled, into halves.
Heat margarine and oil in a large skillet.
Add potatoes and garlic; stir over medium heat until well coated.
Spray a baking sheet with vegetable spray.
Spread potatoes evenly on the sheet; top with the rosemary.
Bake until a deep golden brown, approximately 45 to 50 minutes, stirring occasionally to ensure that potatoes brown evenly.

title: italian haddock
directions: Place fish in buttered oven baking dish. Mix all other ingredients and spread over fish. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or so until cheese is melted and tomatoes are soft.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: In a bowl, mix milk, mayo and dressing mix together. Add cooked pasta, deli meats and tomato. Stir in cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rice stuffed flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and mushrooms in hot margarine.
Mix broth, half and half, cornstarch and dill.
Add to pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Return to boil.
Add carrot and zucchini.
Remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Return to heat on simmer setting for 5 minutes.
Remove again.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Stuff fish with mixture and sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake fish atop any remaining mixture for 20 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Put into large pot.
Add other ingredients, liquid and all.
Cook as long as possible, the longer the better (until all is tender).
Serve with corn chips. Top with sour cream, grated cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce if desired.
(I use cornbread.)

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg together.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to batter.
Blend in blueberries.
Spread in greased and floured cake pan, 8 3/4 x 13 1/2-inch.
Put 1/2 of the batter in pan, then the berries, then the rest of the batter. Put Topping on top of batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add baking powder with flour.
Last add extract.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, cider vinegar and sugar; refrigerate overnight. Toss salad ingredients together.
Pour dressing over salad just before serving and toss.

title: golden waffles
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add 2/3 cup of batter to preheated waffle maker and spread evenly with rubber spatula.
Close lid and bake until light goes out.
Carefully remove waffle.
Respray with oil if sticking occurs.
Makes 4 waffles.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.

title: curried grape and shrimp salad
directions: Cut shrimp into pieces.
Halve grapes and place in a large bowl with cashews.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over shrimp mixture and mix well.
Chill several hours.
Serve on lettuce with crispy French bread.
Prep time:
20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375°F for 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together; add buttermilk, prunes, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: herb bread
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix soft butter with seasonings and juice.
Wrap in foil; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: carrot yogurt cake
directions: Beat carrots, yogurt, orange juice, molasses, raisins, sunflower seeds, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl until well combined.
In a medium bowl, thoroughly combine flour, wheat germ, bran, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold the dry ingredients gradually into the carrot mixture until blended.
Pour batter into a lightly oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Put butter in bowl and gradually add sugar, creaming well. Add egg and beat well.

title: best bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Next day, using soaking water and enough extra water to cover, if necessary, cook beans over medium heat for 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients and cook 1 more hour or until everything is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange oatmeal cake
directions: Bring orange juice to boiling point.
Pour over oats and set aside.
Cream together the butter and sugars until light.
Add eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat until thoroughly blended. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add alternately with oats to creamed mixture.
Stir in grated peel and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done. Remove.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased dish and cook for 45 minutes in approximately 350° oven.

title: beefaroni
directions: Cook beef, onions and green pepper in oil.
When beef is brown and onions cooked add remaining ingredients except for cheese. Pour into casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Make white sauce of milk, butter and flour.
Mix all ingredients, pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 350° until hot and light brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the chicken, soups and Veg-All together.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with biscuits.
Cook in a 300° to 325° oven until biscuits are done.
tags: cream of chicken with mushroom soup

title: special chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend dry oatmeal (quick cooking or old-fashioned) in food processor or blender until powdery.
Mix with flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and oatmeal mixture; mix well.
Mix in chocolate chips, nuts and broken chunks of milk chocolate candy bar.
This requires a very large bowl.
Drop by golf ball sized spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
A small ice cream scoop works well.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in water with salt until done.
Add butter and cheese to hot grits; stir until all melted.
Lightly beat eggs; place in a 1 cup container and add enough milk to make one cup. Add egg mixture to grits; stir in well.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes at high speed.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: realemon touchdown
directions: In pitcher, combine all ingredients, except ice.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Thoroughly combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
With an electric mixer, beat butter or margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
With a spoon, stir in vanilla, orange peel, zucchini and nuts.
Alternately stir dry ingredients and milk into zucchini mixture.

title: mom's banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix wheat germ; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas, milk and banana flavoring.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Mix in nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch well-greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: company apple crisp
directions: Pare, core and cut apples into thin slices.
Lay slices close together in buttered pan.
Mix together white sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour, brown sugar and margarine until
crumbly.
Spread
over
apples and pat firm. Bake in
450° oven
for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: quick frosting
directions: Beat egg white until very stiff, add sugar, slowly beat until the mixture is smooth, add vanilla and spread on cake.

title: cracker jack
directions: Boil sugar, white syrup and margarine until thick and hard. Remove from stove and add salt and soda.
Beat well.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 to 3 times to coat.
Cool.

title: cobble pie dough
directions: Place margarine in baking dish and put in the oven to melt. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and egg, then add milk.
Mix lightly; leave somewhat lumpy.
Too much mixing will toughen the dough.
Pour in can of fruit (any kind of fruit).
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Heat milk. Add beaten egg, sugar and cornstarch moistened with milk. Cook on low to medium heat until thick. Can add coconut to make coconut cream pie or pudding.
Add vanilla and dab of butter after cooked.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix the butter or margarine, brown sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan and cook until 290° on candy thermometer.
Stir often to avoid burning.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda. Stir until foams up.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread onto 2 cookie sheets and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool on cookie sheets 20 minutes.
Stir in a large roaster to break apart so it won't clump up.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: For filling:
Mix first 4 ingredients in a heavy medium saucepan.
Gradually whisk in water.
Set over medium high heat and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Whisk in some yolks in bowl to blend.
Gradually whisk in some hot cornstarch mixture. Return mixture to saucepan, boil until very thick, stirring constantly about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; whisk in juice, butter and lemon peel.
Cool completely.
Spoon filling into crust.
Cover and chill while making meringue.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayo, onion and catsup in small bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in shrimp on low speed.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers or Bugles.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute for 5 minutes margarine, basil, mushrooms, onions and green pepper.
Add to vegetables chicken soup, milk and pimento. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 4 noodles, 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of cottage cheese, 1/2 of chicken and 1/2 of each of cheeses. Repeat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: hearty chili
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Cook until tender and drain.
Cook sausage with onion, green pepper and mushrooms until meat is no longer pink.
Drain and return to pan. Add tomato sauce.
Add cooked potato chunks and beans.
Add water to desired consistency.
Add seasonings to taste.
Simmer until ready to serve.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until the top and edges are golden brown. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Wash and pick over cranberries.
Core and quarter apples. Grind up all ingredients, alternating cranberries, apples and marshmallows.
Add sugar to taste; mix well.
Best when chilled overnight before serving.

title: chicken curry
directions: Add ingredients together.
Cook in large covered casserole at 350° for 1/2 hour, stir and continue cooking approximately another 1/2 hour or until done.
Serve with chutney.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook
chicken in boiling water until tender making sure you have
cups broth left.
Bone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken soup with 1 1/3 cups broth. Set aside.
Repeat
with mushroom soup.
Combine stuffing mix and butter;
reserve
cup
for
garnish.
Spoon
half of remaining
stuffing
mixture
in
lightly
greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top with half of chicken and pour chicken soup over it. Repeat
and
pour
mushroom soup over.
Sprinkle with reserved crunch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush cookies; set aside 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top of finished pie.
Mix remainder of cookies with melted butter and press mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
In large bowl, mix pudding and mix well.
Mix in softened cream cheese until most of lumps are gone.
Pour pudding mixture onto crust and spread evenly. Spread softened Cool Whip on top of pudding evenly.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup crushed cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice with seasoning packet and 2 cups water.
Add both soups undiluted; mix well.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix in large container; mix thoroughly.
For 1 glass of hot chocolate, add 1/2 cup mixture and fill with boiling water.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt 3 Tbsp. butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes and 1/2 of cheese sauce in 2 quart casserole.
Repeat.
Melt 2 Tbsp. butter; stir in bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet fiesta
directions: Slice sausage; set aside.
In a large skillet, saut oil, peppers, onions, garlic, and ginger over medium heat.
Add taco seasoning and water; stir.
Stir in sugar.
Add sausage, beans, and olives; stir.
Simmer 5 min. or until sausage is heated through.
Stir in pasta and simmer an additional 3 min.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling water 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots; fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing with butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon zucchini mixture over that.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: irish shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine flours, then add to butter and sugar.
Press dough into two 8-inch cake pans.
Prick all over with fork.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut cookies while still warm, then let cool and remove from pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix batter and add to pan. Spoon peaches over this.
Pour juice (but not the whole can) all over.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: deluxe pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple, including juice.
Add lemon juice and sugar, stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Mix gelatin in water and add to pineapple mix.
When cool, refrigerate.
When starting to gel, add cheese and fold in whipped cream.
Return to refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Heat water and margarine to boil, remove.
Add flour and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Spread in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread over bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes and let cool. Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate fudge.

title: caldereta
directions: Heat oil and brown the garlic.
Remove the garlic and saute onion and tomatoes, then add the meat and seasonings.
Cook until the meat is almost tender.
Add potatoes.
When potatoes are almost cooked, thicken the sauce.
Add sliced pepper and peas. Serve hot.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and pour off grease.
Add margarine and sprinkle with flour; mix together.
In large pot, place all other ingredients.
I put the tomatoes in the blender.
Add meat mixture; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer; cook for 1 hour.
Stir often to keep from sticking.

title: friday meat loaf
directions: Put cheese and beans together.
Add seasoning, crumbs to make stiff and melted butter or milk to moisten if dry.
Bake and serve with tomato sauce.

title: tina's cheese dip
directions: Fry up the sausage; drain off all of the grease.
In a saucepan, melt the cheese and add the salsa and sausage.
Mix well and serve hot with tortilla chips off to the side.
It's a good thing.

title: white pull candy
directions: Oil a platter with vegetable oil.
Place sugar, water, vinegar and butter in a deep saucepan.
Stir over low heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Increase the heat slightly and cook the mixture, without stirring, until a smooth amount will form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from fire and add vanilla.
Stir only enough to blend the mixture.
Pour the mixture onto the lightly oiled platter.
Let it cool until a dent can be made in it when pressed with a finger.
Gather it into a lump and pull it with the fingertips until it is light and porous.
Dip your hands frequently into cold water to prevent the candy from sticking to them.
Roll into long thin strips and cut into 1-inch pieces. Place the candy in a tightly covered tin if you wish it to become creamy.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle jello	over cottage cheese and mix.
Add other ingredients. Let cool in refrigerator.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Pour sherry over dates.
Let stand 1 hour; stuff each date with an almond, walnut or pecan half.
Roll in tinted coconut or powdered sugar.
(Dates soaked in wine, dry sherry, sprinkled with pale green coconut; or frosted with Christmas colors, nuts buried in their delicious middle.)

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Bring cream to boil; remove from stove.
Add sugar and flour; stir well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chinese pot pie
directions: Put in layers in casserole dish potatoes, beef, onion and corn.
After each layer add salt and pepper to taste and a little flour for thickening.
After casserole is filled, pour beef bouillon over top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or longer, depending on your oven.

title: great homemade biscuits
directions: Blend flour and Crisco.
Add buttermilk.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut and bake at 475° to 500° about 8 minutes.
Use ungreased pan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper in a shallow dish.
Coat both sides of chicken in the melted butter; then coat both sides with bread crumb mixture.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Cook at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes (until chicken is done).

title: louie's chili
directions: Brown meat in butter. Add remainder of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat well all ingredients, except milk, then add evaporated milk.
Pour into greased and floured pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cherry sweet potatoes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cherry filling, allspice and pepper.
Add sweet potatoes and mix gently.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 10-inch tube pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and butter until smooth.
Then add sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and baking powder together.
Rotate flour mixture and milk, then add flavorings. Mix until all is smooth.
Bake in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Boil giblets in water and set aside.
Pour fat from pan chicken was cooked in.
Add flour to 3 tablespoons of fat and stir until brown.
Add stock from boiled giblets.
Stir until smooth and thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine and spread on English muffin halves.
Freeze for later use.
When ready to serve, cut each half into wedges (8 per half). Broil on cookie sheet 2 to 3 minutes until hot and bubbly.
A great make-ahead appetizer!

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator to serve with fresh fruit for dipping.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with milk.
Mix together sugar, flour and nutmeg and stir into milk and egg mixture.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter and cover with lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve slightly warm.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes.
When done, remove skin and bones. Break chicken into small pieces. Boil broccoli until near done (10 to 15 minutes).
Arrange chicken in layers in 3-quart casserole dish. Break off broccoli pieces and cover chicken to make second layer.
Next use 3/4 of the cheese to make third layer.
Next mix mushroom soup (no water), mayonnaise and lemon juice together. Blend well.
Pour over the mixture.
Add buttered bread crumbs to cover top and sprinkle balance of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: classic pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin strips, then into 1-inch squares.
Coat with 1 tablespoon stir-fry sauce.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a hot wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add meat and stir-fry 1 minute; remove.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in same pan.
Add peppers and onions; stir-fry 5 minutes. Stir in beef and 1/4 cup stir-fry sauce.
Cook and stir just until beef and vegetables are coated with sauce.
Serve immediately with rice.

title: blueberry mold
directions: Heat 1 cup cream and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add Knox gelatine to 1/4 cup cold water to soften.
Add to cream and sugar.
Cool, then add sour cream and vanilla.
Chill until firm.
Mix together 1 cup boiling water, raspberry jello and blueberries and pour over the cream mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: boiled country ham
directions: To cook, place the whole ham in a large pan, skin side down. Cover with fresh water.
Simmer with pan covered until temperature reaches 160° (about 15 to 18 minutes per pound).

title: ooey gooey bars or cheese bars
directions: Mix in oblong cake pan the first 3 ingredients and let set for about 5 minutes.
Pat thin on bottom of pan.
Mix in mixing bowl the next 3 ingredients.
Alternate:
sprinkle chips on top of cake mix batter then pour cream cheese mixture over them.
Sprinkle this top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool and then cut into squares.
May use a can of coconut on top of chocolate chips.
Grease pan with butter.
Better with black walnuts.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients to moisten. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Yields approximately 6 to 7 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: texas style tortilla soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in a Dutch oven until onion is tender, but not brown. Drain well. Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes, reserving juice. Add tomatoes and juice to Dutch oven with remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour. Add tortillas and continue simmering 10 minutes. Ladle into soup bowls, then sprinkle with cheese.

title: pot roast
directions: Cook 1/2 hour per pound at 325°, covered in a Dutch oven.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Simmer potatoes, onions, and celery in water until tender. Using a potato masher, mash vegetables until only bits of potato are left. Add remaining ingredients, cover, and simmer until thick and creamy.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar, lemon juice and salt. Add celery and nuts. Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream. Gently fold into apple mixture. Chill and serve in lettuce-lined bowls. Makes 6 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs, milk and flavoring.
Mix well. Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a round cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until it threads in heavy pan.
Add 1 pound peanuts; cook until peanuts spread, stirring constantly. Add 1 teaspoon soda and stir until it reaches color you want. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan sugar, milk, marshmallows, oleo and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir until completely melted chocolate pieces.
Stir in pecans and vanilla. Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and pick beans.
In a large pot, combine beans and water over medium-high heat.
As beans begin to cook, add all remaining ingredients and stir well.
When heated well, turn on low and cook until beans are tender and creamy, stirring occasionally. Water may need to be added during cooking.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Stir Miracle Whip, lemon juice, grated peel and dill weed together.
Place fish on greased grill or rack of broiler pan. Brush with half of the sauce. Grill or broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue to grill or broil another 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Serves 4.

title: lima bean - corn pie
directions: I used broccoli instead of beans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts. Cream shortening and gradually add sugar.
Add the eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: creamy cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Mix until well blended.
Add sour cream and beat in an electric mixer until creamy.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lo mein
directions: Brown uncooked noodles in margarine.
Add other ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: fruit and nut stuffing for roast wild fowl
directions: Mix ingredients and stuff bird.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir in garlic, Bisquick, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs just until mixture is blended.
Fold in zucchini.
Fry at medium heat using 2 tablespoons of mixture for each round.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Use Dutch oven size boiler; heat oil.
Add flour; begin making your roux.
Stir flour and oil mixture until it begins to brown, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes (adjust heat as needed). Let roux darken until it looks like it is going to burn.
When roux is dark enough, add 1 cup of boiling water (roux will thicken).
Stir in bell peppers and onion and cook for 10 minutes. Add another cup of boiling water and stir in gumbo file, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper.
Cook for another 15 minutes and add shrimp; cook 15 minutes and add okra.
Continue to cook over medium heat at a slow simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add the rest of ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake slowly, starting at 250°, then increase oven to 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. If mixture is dry, add a little water to moisten. Form into cakes and fry in 1/2-inch cooking oil. Cook on both sides until golden brown.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple or oranges.
Dissolve gelatin with hot water; add fruit and chill until slightly firm.
Stir in sour cream; chill overnight.
Serves 12.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and beat in milk.
Stir in gelatin.
Add undrained pineapple.
Chill.

title: italian baked eggplant(serves 6)
directions: Layer
eggplant
slices
on
paper
towels.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Let drain
about
40 minutes.
In a medium bowl combine bread crumbs
with
cup Parmesan cheese.
In another bowl combine eggs
and water.
Dip each eggplant slice into eggs, then into
bread
crumb mixture.
Brown eggplant in hot oil on both
sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread evenly 1/2 cup pasta sauce in a baking dish.
Layer half the eggplant slices, 1 cup pasta sauce and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers. Cover with foil.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given in a large 12 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Combine Miracle Whip and sugar; spread evenly over salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 3 cups.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Put applesauce in an ungreased baking pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, butter and spice.
Spoon over applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zippy tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna; break up into flakes.
Gently stir in mayonnaise, yogurt, olives, peppers, green onion and cilantro.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Hot peppers provide the zip.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very, very large bowl.
Store in covered containers.
